# RDFS Schema for Business: Real Estate

@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix ind: <http://datamodel.lakehouse.org/business/real_estate#> .

# --- Root Business Class ---
ind:Business rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:label 'Business' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Root class for all business entities' .

# --- Specific Business: Real Estate ---
ind:RealEstate rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Business ;
    rdfs:label 'Real Estate' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Real Estate is a capital-intensive industry encompassing commercial and residential property sales, leasing, valuations, property management, development, and investment advisory services for owners, investors, and tenants.' .

# --- Domain Classes ---
ind:Property rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:RealEstate ;
    rdfs:label 'Property' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core operational domain and master registry for all real estate assets — commercial, residential, and mixed-use properties, buildings, land parcels, units, and spaces. Owns physical attributes (GLA, NLA, SQF/SQM, FAR), building specifications, GIS coordinates, zoning classifications, COO status, LEED/BREEAM certifications, BIM references, title information, and ownership hierarchy. Single source of truth for every asset the enterprise owns, manages, or brokers.' .

ind:Tenant rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:RealEstate ;
    rdfs:label 'Tenant' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for all tenant and prospect identities across commercial and residential portfolios. Manages tenant profiles, contact hierarchies, credit profiles, HOA memberships, occupancy history, lease history, and CRM-linked prospect pipelines. Supports both B2B corporate tenants and B2C residential occupants with comprehensive tenant lifecycle and relationship management.' .

ind:Lease rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:RealEstate ;
    rdfs:label 'Lease' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Governs the full lifecycle of lease agreements — LOIs, executed leases, amendments, renewals, and terminations. Owns lease terms (NNN, gross, modified gross), TI allowances, CAM schedules, rent escalation clauses, WALT/WALE metrics, SNDA agreements, and renewal options. Authoritative source for ASC 842 / IFRS 16 lease accounting data including lease classification, measurement, and disclosure.' .

ind:Transaction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:RealEstate ;
    rdfs:label 'Transaction' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records all property acquisition, disposition, and sale events — purchase agreements, closing statements, title transfers (ALTA), REO transactions, 1031 exchanges, and financing transactions. Tracks deal economics including PSF pricing, LTV ratios, earnest money, cash flows, and settlement details. Integrates with MLS and CoStar comparable sales data.' .

ind:Owner rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:RealEstate ;
    rdfs:label 'Owner' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for property owner and investor identities — individual owners, institutional investors, REITs, joint-venture entities, and partnerships. Manages ownership structures, equity stakes, beneficial ownership records, investor onboarding KYC data, contact information, and ownership agreements. Distinct from tenant domain; owners may also be investors tracked in the investment domain.' .

ind:Valuation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:RealEstate ;
    rdfs:label 'Valuation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages property appraisals, BPOs, CMAs, and DCF-based valuations. Stores CAP rates, NOI inputs, IRR/NPV outputs, GAV/NAV calculations, and Argus Enterprise model references. Tracks appraisal history, certified appraiser credentials (Appraisal Institute), IVSC-compliant methodology metadata, and market value assessments supporting investment decision-making and financial reporting.' .

ind:Development rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:RealEstate ;
    rdfs:label 'Development' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks real estate development and construction oversight from entitlement through COO issuance. Manages Procore project data, RFIs, submittals, construction budgets, CAPEX draw schedules, FAR compliance, BIM model references, permits, zoning approvals, contractor management, and milestone tracking. Covers ground-up development and major capital improvement programs.' .

ind:Investment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:RealEstate ;
    rdfs:label 'Investment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages real estate investment portfolios, fund structures, and investment performance. Captures investment vehicles (REITs, funds, partnerships, CMBS/RMBS), portfolio composition, AUM, investment strategies, IRR/NPV/ROI calculations, FFO/AFFO reporting, NAV/GAV calculations, and investment advisory relationships. Supports institutional and individual investor portfolio management with comprehensive performance analytics.' .

ind:Maintenance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:RealEstate ;
    rdfs:label 'Maintenance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Owns all facility operations and building services data — work orders, preventive maintenance schedules, HVAC and O&M records, tenant service requests, vendor dispatch, service contracts, and asset condition tracking. Sourced from Building Engines CMMS. Tracks CAPEX vs. OPEX classification for maintenance activities, OSHA safety compliance, and building equipment lifecycle.' .

ind:Brokerage rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:RealEstate ;
    rdfs:label 'Brokerage' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages sales and leasing brokerage activity including deal pipelines, listing agreements, commission structures, co-broker arrangements, MLS/CoStar listing syndication, and agent/broker licensing. Tracks production metrics, prospect management, brokerage agreements, and Salesforce CRM deal stages from prospect to close. Supports both buy-side and sell-side brokerage operations.' .

ind:Finance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:RealEstate ;
    rdfs:label 'Finance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Enterprise financial backbone covering GL, AP, AR, budgeting, forecasting, and financial reporting as sourced from Yardi Voyager and SAP S/4HANA. Owns cost centers, chart of accounts, NOI statements, EGI/PGI/GOI calculations, EBITDA roll-ups, DSCR calculations, cash management, financial consolidation, and SOX-compliant financial controls. Authoritative source for all property-level and portfolio-level P&L data.' .

ind:Compliance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:RealEstate ;
    rdfs:label 'Compliance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages regulatory compliance obligations across the portfolio — EPA environmental assessments, OSHA building safety records, HUD fair housing filings, GDPR tenant data privacy controls, SEC reporting for publicly traded REITs, ESG metrics, LEED/BREEAM certification tracking, audit trails, and regulatory filing deadlines. Supports multi-jurisdictional compliance across federal, state, and local regulations.' .

ind:Workforce rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:RealEstate ;
    rdfs:label 'Workforce' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages human capital data for property managers, asset managers, brokers, leasing agents, construction staff, and corporate employees. Sourced from ADP Workforce Now. Covers employee profiles, payroll, benefits, time and attendance, licensing/certification tracking (broker licenses, appraiser credentials), talent management, roles, and workforce planning across property management, development, and corporate functions.' .

ind:Reference rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:RealEstate ;
    rdfs:label 'Reference' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Centralized repository for all enterprise reference and lookup data — property types, lease types, transaction types, geographic hierarchies, market segments, zoning codes, currency codes, unit-of-measure standards (PSF, SQF/SQM), industry classification codes, and business taxonomies. Provides controlled vocabularies and standardized code sets that ensure data consistency across all operational and analytical domains.' .

ind:Marketing rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:RealEstate ;
    rdfs:label 'Marketing' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages property marketing campaigns, digital listings, lead generation, market research, brand management, and advertising spend across commercial and residential portfolios. Tracks marketing channels, campaign performance, lead attribution, and competitive market intelligence.' .

ind:Insurance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:RealEstate ;
    rdfs:label 'Insurance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages property and liability insurance policies, claims, risk assessments, certificates of insurance (COI), and loss run reports across the real estate portfolio. Tracks policy renewals, premium payments, coverage limits, deductibles, and insured values for all asset types.' .

# --- Data Product Classes (Tables) ---
ind:Owner rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Owner ;
    rdfs:label 'Owner' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT master registry for all property owner and investor identities — individuals, institutional investors, REITs, corporations, trusts, family offices, and sovereign wealth funds. Captures legal entity type, registration details, domicile jurisdiction, tax identification numbers (EIN/SSN/TIN), beneficial ownership flags, AUM classification, onboarding status, and owner preferences (target asset classes, risk tolerance, IRR hurdles, ESG mandates). This is the authoritative golden record for every owner entity across the portfolio, sourced from Yardi Voyager and MRI Software.' .

ind:OwnerContact rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Owner ;
    rdfs:label 'Owner Contact' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Contact information records for owner entities — primary and secondary contacts, mailing addresses, email addresses, phone numbers, preferred communication channels, and contact role types (primary, legal, financial, operational). Supports multi-contact hierarchies for institutional owners with multiple authorized representatives.' .

ind:OwnerOwnershipInterest rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Owner ;
    rdfs:label 'Owner Ownership Interest' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records the equity stake or ownership interest held by an owner in a specific property or investment vehicle, including full status lifecycle and audit history. Captures ownership percentage, interest type (fee simple, leasehold, fractional, beneficial), acquisition date, cost basis, vesting schedule, co-ownership arrangement flags, current status (pending, active, encumbered, disputed, transferred, terminated), and complete status transition history with previous status, new status, effective dates, change reasons, changed-by user, and supporting document references. Central to tracking fractional ownership, JV structures, and REIT unit holdings at the property level. Enables full ownership lifecycle traceability for legal, compliance, and audit purposes.' .

ind:OwnershipStructure rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Owner ;
    rdfs:label 'Ownership Structure' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the legal and organizational structure through which ownership is held — single owner, joint venture, limited partnership (LP), LLC, REIT, tenancy-in-common (TIC), or trust. Captures structure type, formation date, governing jurisdiction, operating agreement reference, managing member designation, and dissolution date. Enables modeling of complex multi-tier ownership hierarchies.' .

ind:BeneficialOwner rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Owner ;
    rdfs:label 'Beneficial Owner' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks ultimate beneficial ownership (UBO) records for entities where legal ownership differs from beneficial ownership — required for FinCEN Corporate Transparency Act (CTA) compliance, AML/KYC regulations, and FATF standards. Captures beneficial owner identity, ownership threshold percentage (25%+ per CTA), control type (direct/indirect), verification status, regulatory disclosure flags, and filing reference numbers. Critical for institutional investors, trusts, shell companies, and multi-tier holding structures subject to mandatory UBO reporting.' .

ind:KycProfile rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Owner ;
    rdfs:label 'Kyc Profile' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Comprehensive Know Your Customer (KYC) onboarding, due diligence, and compliance lifecycle record for owner and investor entities. Stores identity verification status, AML screening results, PEP flags, sanctions screening status, risk rating, accredited investor certification, and last review date. Includes collected document inventory (passport, articles of incorporation, trust deed, tax certificates) with document type, issuing authority, issue/expiry dates, verification method, verification outcome, and storage references. Tracks compliance lifecycle events including KYC renewal due dates, beneficial ownership re-certification, FATCA/CRS reporting submissions, FIRPTA withholding events, AML re-screening triggers, event outcomes, and responsible parties. Supports regulatory compliance with BSA, FinCEN CTA, GDPR, and SEC requirements. Provides full audit trail for regulatory examinations.' .

ind:OwnerAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Owner ;
    rdfs:label 'Owner Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Ownership and investor agreements governing the relationship between the owner entity and the property management/asset management firm — including property management agreements (PMAs), asset management mandates, JV operating agreements, co-ownership agreements, SNDA agreements, and subscription agreements. Captures agreement type, effective and expiration dates, governing law, fee structures (management fee %, incentive fee tiers), termination clauses, renewal terms, and DocuSign CLM execution reference.' .

ind:OwnerDistribution rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Owner ;
    rdfs:label 'Owner Distribution' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for income and capital distributions made to owners from property operations, including disbursement banking instructions. This is the owner-perspective distribution record, distinct from finance domain GL entries which record the accounting impact. Captures distribution type (NOI, FFO/AFFO, capital gain, return of capital, preferred return), calculation period, gross amount, withholding tax, net disbursement amount, distribution date, payment method, and Yardi GL cross-reference. Also stores owner bank account and disbursement details: bank name, account type, routing number (masked/tokenized), SWIFT/IBAN for international owners, preferred disbursement method, and account verification status. Supports investor reporting, tax K-1 preparation, and AP reconciliation.' .

ind:CapitalContribution rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Owner ;
    rdfs:label 'Capital Contribution' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for equity capital contributions made by owners and investors into properties, JV structures, or investment vehicles — recorded from the owner/investor perspective. Distinct from finance domain GL entries which record the accounting debit/credit impact. Captures contribution date, amount, currency, contribution type (initial equity, capital call response, preferred equity injection, co-invest), ownership percentage impact, funding source, wire confirmation reference, and capital account balance impact. Tracks CAPEX funding events, equity waterfall inputs, and unfunded commitment drawdowns. Linked to ownership_interest for pro-rata tracking.' .

ind:OwnershipTransfer rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Owner ;
    rdfs:label 'Ownership Transfer' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records the transfer of ownership interests between parties — including equity stake transfers, JV buyouts, inheritance transfers, 1031 exchanges, and foreclosure/REO transfers. Captures transfer type, transferor (owner FK), transferee (owner FK), transfer date, consideration amount, transfer percentage, title instrument reference, ALTA settlement statement reference, recording jurisdiction, and tax implications. Distinct from the transaction domain which records full property acquisition/disposition events; this product tracks interest-level transfers within existing ownership structures.' .

ind:TaxRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Owner ;
    rdfs:label 'Tax Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for owner-perspective tax records — property tax obligations by jurisdiction, tax identification numbers, withholding tax rates for foreign owners (FIRPTA), tax treaty elections, K-1 partnership income allocations, and annual tax reporting status. Distinct from finance domain tax accounting (GL tax entries) and compliance domain regulatory filings; this product captures the owner-specific tax profile and obligations. Captures tax year, jurisdiction, tax type, assessed amount, filing status, and SAP S/4HANA tax cross-reference. Supports SOX compliance and SEC reporting for publicly traded REITs.' .

ind:EntityHierarchy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Owner ;
    rdfs:label 'Entity Hierarchy' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Models the parent-child organizational hierarchy among owner entities — holding companies, subsidiaries, SPVs, fund-of-funds structures, and REIT umbrella partnerships. Captures parent entity, child entity, hierarchy level, relationship type (wholly owned, majority controlled, minority interest), effective date, and consolidation flag. Enables roll-up reporting of AUM, NAV, and GAV across complex multi-tier ownership structures.' .

ind:Accreditation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Owner ;
    rdfs:label 'Accreditation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Investor accreditation and qualification records for owners participating in private real estate offerings — SEC Regulation D accredited investor status, qualified purchaser status, qualified institutional buyer (QIB) status, and ERISA plan investor classification. Captures accreditation type, certification date, expiry date, verification method, certifying party, and renewal status. Required for private placement compliance.' .

ind:PowerOfAttorney rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Owner ;
    rdfs:label 'Power Of Attorney' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Power of attorney (POA) and authorized signatory records for owner entities — designating individuals or entities authorized to act on behalf of the owner in property transactions, lease executions, loan closings, and financial matters. Captures grantor (owner FK), grantee (authorized agent), scope of authority (general, limited, durable, springing), effective and expiry dates, notarization status, recording jurisdiction, revocation status, and DocuSign CLM execution reference. Critical for institutional owners, trust structures, and estate planning scenarios.' .

ind:WorkOrder rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Maintenance ;
    rdfs:label 'Work Order' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core transactional entity representing a maintenance work order issued for a property or building asset. Captures the full lifecycle from creation through completion — including work type (corrective, preventive, emergency), priority level, CAPEX vs. OPEX classification, assigned trade/vendor, scheduled and actual completion dates, and safety compliance flags (OSHA, HSE, or equivalent jurisdiction-specific standards). Includes embedded cost line items for labor (technician hours, trade type, hourly rates, overtime) and materials (parts consumed, quantities, unit costs, supplier references). Tracks status transitions as an immutable audit trail for SLA breach analysis and compliance. Sourced from CMMS platforms (e.g., Building Engines, Corrigo, Angus). The primary operational record for all facility maintenance activity.' .

ind:ServiceRequest rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Maintenance ;
    rdfs:label 'Service Request' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tenant-initiated service request submitted through a tenant portal, help desk, or mobile app. Captures the originating tenant, property, suite, request category (HVAC, plumbing, electrical, janitorial, access), description, urgency, submission timestamp, SLA target response and resolution times, and current status. Distinct from a work order — a service request is the tenant-facing intake record that may spawn one or more work orders. Supports tenant relationship management and CAM charge-back tracking.' .

ind:PmSchedule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Maintenance ;
    rdfs:label 'Pm Schedule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Preventive Maintenance (PM) schedule master record defining the recurring maintenance program for a building asset or equipment item. Stores the PM frequency (daily, weekly, monthly, annual), task checklist template, assigned trade category, estimated labor hours, required parts, next due date, last completed date, and compliance flag (OSHA/HSE, LEED, manufacturer warranty). Drives automated work order generation in the CMMS. Distinct from a work order — this is the standing schedule, not the execution record.' .

ind:BuildingAsset rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Maintenance ;
    rdfs:label 'Building Asset' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master registry of all physical building equipment and infrastructure assets subject to maintenance management — HVAC units, elevators, boilers, generators, fire suppression systems, electrical panels, plumbing systems, roofing, and other O&M-tracked components. Captures asset tag, manufacturer, model, serial number, installation date, expected useful life, replacement cost, current condition rating, and BIM reference ID. Includes warranty records (manufacturer, extended, labor warranties with coverage dates and claim history) and periodic condition assessment history (condition ratings, remaining useful life estimates, recommended capital replacement year). SSOT for maintainable building equipment within the maintenance domain.' .

ind:VendorDispatch rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Maintenance ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor Dispatch' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of a vendor or contractor dispatched to a property to fulfill a work order. Captures the dispatched vendor, dispatch timestamp, estimated arrival window, actual arrival and departure times, work performed summary, sign-off status, and invoice reference. Tracks vendor performance against SLA commitments and supports CAM reconciliation for billable maintenance costs. Multiple dispatches may occur per work order (e.g., return visits, multi-trade coordination).' .

ind:ServiceContract rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Maintenance ;
    rdfs:label 'Service Contract' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for a maintenance service contract or vendor agreement governing recurring facility services — HVAC maintenance contracts, elevator service agreements, janitorial contracts, landscaping, pest control, and security. Captures contract number, vendor, covered properties, service scope, contract start/end dates, renewal terms, annual contract value, SLA terms, insurance certificate requirements, and CAPEX vs. OPEX classification. Distinct from individual work orders — this is the standing contractual framework.' .

ind:OpsInspection rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Maintenance ;
    rdfs:label 'Ops Inspection' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Record of a formal property or equipment inspection event — fire safety inspections, elevator certifications, HVAC commissioning, roof inspections, ADA/accessibility compliance walkthroughs, and workplace safety audits (OSHA, HSE, or equivalent). Captures inspection type, inspecting party (internal or third-party), inspection date, pass/fail result, and regulatory citation reference. Includes individual deficiency findings with severity classification (critical, major, minor), affected asset or area, recommended corrective action, responsible party, target and actual remediation dates, and remediation work order references. Supports regulatory compliance, certificate of occupancy maintenance obligations, and tracking of open deficiencies through to resolution.' .

ind:CapexProject rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Maintenance ;
    rdfs:label 'Capex Project' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Capital expenditure project record for major building improvements, equipment replacements, or infrastructure upgrades classified as CAPEX rather than OPEX. Captures project name, description, property reference, asset reference, approved budget, actual spend to date, project start and end dates, funding source, approval authority, ERP project system reference, and capitalization date. Distinct from routine work orders — CAPEX projects involve asset capitalization and fixed asset creation in the GL.' .

ind:PartsInventory rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Maintenance ;
    rdfs:label 'Parts Inventory' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record of maintenance parts, supplies, and consumables stocked at a property or central warehouse for building maintenance operations. Captures part number, description, unit of measure, current on-hand quantity, reorder point, reorder quantity, preferred supplier, unit cost, storage location, and asset compatibility. Supports parts availability for work order fulfillment, procurement planning, and min/max inventory management. SSOT for facility O&M inventory within the maintenance domain.' .

ind:SlaPolicy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Maintenance ;
    rdfs:label 'Sla Policy' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Service Level Agreement policy record defining response and resolution time targets for maintenance work orders and tenant service requests by priority tier, property class, and request category. Captures SLA name, applicable property types, priority level (emergency, urgent, routine, planned), target response time, target resolution time, escalation rules, penalty terms, and effective date range. Supports multi-jurisdiction property management standards and can accommodate varying SLA frameworks across regions. Drives SLA compliance tracking and tenant satisfaction reporting.' .

ind:BillableCharge rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Maintenance ;
    rdfs:label 'Billable Charge' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Billable maintenance charge record generated when maintenance costs are recoverable from tenants under NNN or modified gross lease structures as part of CAM reconciliation. Captures the originating work order or service contract, tenant reference, charge amount, charge category (HVAC, janitorial, repairs, landscaping), billing period, CAM pool allocation method, and invoice reference in the property management accounting system. Bridges the maintenance domain to the finance and lease domains for CAM charge-back processing.' .

ind:SafetyIncident rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Maintenance ;
    rdfs:label 'Safety Incident' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Safety incident or near-miss event occurring at a managed property during maintenance or facility operations activities. Captures incident date and time, property location, incident type (injury, near-miss, property damage, environmental), description, injured party details, regulatory recordability flag (OSHA 300 log in US, RIDDOR in UK, or equivalent jurisdiction-specific reporting), first aid vs. medical treatment classification, root cause, corrective actions taken, and regulatory filing reference. Supports workplace safety compliance and building safety governance across jurisdictions.' .

ind:PmExecution rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Maintenance ;
    rdfs:label 'Pm Execution' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Execution record of a completed preventive maintenance task instance generated from a PM schedule. Captures the parent PM schedule reference, execution date, technician assigned, actual vs. planned duration, checklist completion status (each task item pass/fail/N/A), findings noted, and parts consumed. Records whether a corrective work order was spawned from findings. Provides the historical audit trail of PM compliance and supports equipment reliability analysis and mean-time-between-failure (MTBF) calculations.' .

ind:Listing rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Listing' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all property listings managed by the brokerage — commercial and residential, for sale or lease. Captures listing type (exclusive, open, co-exclusive), listing status (active, pending, expired, withdrawn, sold/leased), MLS/CoStar syndication flags, listing price/rate PSF, GLA/NLA, property class, submarket, listing start and expiration dates, days on market, and the originating source system (Salesforce CRM, CoStar). Serves as the SSOT for all brokerage-managed property offerings.' .

ind:ListingAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Listing Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Formal contractual agreement between the brokerage and a property owner/seller authorizing the brokerage to market and transact on their behalf. Captures agreement type (exclusive right to sell, exclusive agency, open listing, net listing), term start and end dates, agreed commission rate or flat fee, co-broker split authorization, listing price, and execution status. Sourced from DocuSign CLM and Salesforce CRM. Distinct from a lease agreement (owned by the lease domain) — this governs the brokerage engagement itself.' .

ind:BrokerageDeal rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Brokerage Deal' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core transactional record representing a brokerage deal from prospect to close, sourced from Salesforce CRM opportunity pipeline. Tracks deal type (sale, lease, sublease, assignment), deal stage (prospect, LOI, under contract, due diligence, closed, dead), property reference, deal size (SF/SQM, total consideration), projected and actual close dates, probability percentage, deal source, assigned broker/agent, and exclusivity periods. Includes immutable stage transition history as child records capturing prior stage, new stage, transition timestamp, reason for change, and triggering broker — enabling pipeline velocity analysis, stage duration tracking, and CRM workflow compliance auditing. Serves as the SSOT for brokerage deal pipeline activity and deal stage audit trail across buy-side and sell-side operations.' .

ind:BrokerageProspect rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Brokerage Prospect' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Brokerage-specific record for a prospective buyer, tenant, or investor tracked in the Salesforce CRM deal pipeline before they become a confirmed counterparty on a deal. Captures prospect type (buyer, tenant, investor, owner/seller), contact details, requirement profile (target SF range, budget PSF, preferred submarket, property type, move-in timeline), source of introduction (referral, cold call, marketing campaign, CoStar lead, walk-in), qualification status (unqualified, MQL, SQL, nurturing, converted, lost), assigned broker, last contact date, next follow-up date, and CRM lead/contact reference. Distinct from the tenant domain\'s tenant master — this is a pre-transaction brokerage pipeline entity that converts into a deal counterparty upon qualification.' .

ind:Showing rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Showing' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records each property showing or tour event conducted as part of the brokerage sales or leasing process. Captures showing date and time, property and listing reference, prospect or counterparty attending, broker conducting the showing, showing type (in-person, virtual), feedback notes, follow-up action required, and outcome (interested, not interested, offer pending). Sourced from Salesforce CRM activity tracking.' .

ind:NegotiationInstrument rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Negotiation Instrument' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Pre-contract negotiation instrument record capturing all formal offers and letters of intent submitted during the brokerage deal process. Covers LOIs (non-binding), binding purchase offers, lease proposals, and counter-offers via a type discriminator. Records submission date, expiration date, proposed terms (price or rent PSF, lease term, TI allowance, CAM structure, NNN vs gross), contingencies (financing, inspection, due diligence period), earnest money deposit, counterparty identity, property reference, deal reference, negotiation round, binding/non-binding flag, and status (submitted, countered, accepted, rejected, expired, withdrawn). Serves as the SSOT for all pre-contract negotiation instruments in the brokerage deal lifecycle — from initial non-binding LOI through binding offer acceptance. Replaces the need for a separate offer entity by using a type discriminator to distinguish instrument types.' .

ind:Commission rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Commission' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record defining the commission structure and earned commission for each brokerage deal or listing agreement. Captures commission type (percentage of consideration, flat fee, PSF-based), gross commission amount, co-broker split percentage, referral fee deductions, net commission to house, commission trigger event (lease execution, closing, LOI acceptance), payment schedule (upfront, installment), and commission status (pending, approved, paid, disputed). Sourced from Yardi Voyager AR and Salesforce CRM.' .

ind:CommissionSplit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Commission Split' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Detailed allocation and disbursement record breaking down how a gross commission is split among participating brokers, agents, co-brokers, and the brokerage house, and tracking actual payment execution through to settlement. Captures recipient type (in-house agent, co-broker firm, referral partner, brokerage house), recipient identity, split percentage, split dollar amount, override adjustments, disbursement date, payment method (wire, ACH, check), bank account reference, disbursement status (scheduled, processed, failed, reversed), and Yardi Voyager AP transaction reference. Serves as the SSOT for both commission allocation and disbursement — each row represents one payee\'s share of a commission and the payment lifecycle for that share. Supports multi-party commission disbursement workflows, agent production tracking, 1099 reporting, and provides the financial audit trail for all commission payments.' .

ind:CoBrokerAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Co Broker Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Formal co-brokerage arrangement record between the listing brokerage and a cooperating broker firm for a specific deal or listing. Captures cooperating broker firm name, license number, designated agent, agreed co-broker commission split percentage, SNDA requirements, MLS cooperation flag, agreement execution date, and deal or listing reference. Governs the legal and financial terms of inter-firm brokerage cooperation.' .

ind:BrokerageBroker rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Brokerage Broker' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for licensed brokers and agents operating within or on behalf of the brokerage. Captures broker type (principal broker, associate broker, managing broker, leasing agent, buyer\'s agent, seller\'s agent), state license number, license expiration date, NAR/CCIM/SIOR membership status, MLS membership ID, designated market areas, production tier (based on GCI thresholds), hire date, employment type (W-2, 1099 independent contractor), team/desk assignment, and commission plan reference. Distinct from the workforce domain\'s employee record — this is the brokerage-specific professional identity, licensing, and production tracking record. Serves as the SSOT for broker identity referenced by deals, listings, commissions, showings, and prospect assignments.' .

ind:BrokerLicense rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Broker License' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks all real estate licenses held by each broker or agent, including state-by-state licensing, license type (salesperson, broker, managing broker), issuing authority, license number, issue date, expiration date, renewal status, CE (continuing education) hours completed, and disciplinary flags. Supports NAR and state regulatory compliance. A broker may hold multiple licenses across jurisdictions.' .

ind:MlsSyndication rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Mls Syndication' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks the syndication status of each listing to external platforms including MLS (via RETS/RESO Web API), CoStar, LoopNet, Zillow, Realtor.com, CREXi, and other listing portals. Captures target platform, syndication status (active, pending, failed, withdrawn, suppressed), external listing ID on the target platform, syndication date, last refresh timestamp, data feed type (IDX, VOW, RETS), RESO Data Dictionary compliance flag, and any platform-specific validation errors. Sourced from CoStar Suite and MLS data feeds. Supports multi-channel listing distribution management and ensures RESO/IDX compliance across syndication targets.' .

ind:Referral rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Referral' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records inbound and outbound referral arrangements between the brokerage and external parties (other brokers, relocation companies, affinity networks). Captures referral direction (inbound, outbound), referring party name and firm, referred prospect or deal, referral fee percentage or flat amount, referral agreement date, referral status (pending, active, closed, paid), and deal outcome. Supports referral fee tracking and network relationship management.' .

ind:BuyerRepresentation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Buyer Representation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Buyer or tenant representation agreement record formalizing the brokerage\'s engagement to represent a buyer or tenant in a property search and acquisition or leasing transaction. Captures representation type (exclusive buyer rep, exclusive tenant rep, non-exclusive), client identity, target property criteria (type, size, submarket, budget), agreement term, agreed commission or fee structure, exclusivity clause, and agreement status. Sourced from DocuSign CLM.' .

ind:BrokerageDealDocument rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Brokerage Deal Document' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks all documents associated with a brokerage deal throughout its lifecycle — LOIs, offers, counter-offers, purchase and sale agreements, lease abstracts, commission agreements, co-broker agreements, closing statements, and regulatory disclosures. Captures document type, document name, version number, execution status (draft, pending signature, executed, voided), DocuSign envelope ID, upload timestamp, deal reference, and retention expiration date. Supports state-mandated document retention requirements (typically 3-7 years depending on jurisdiction) and provides the audit trail for deal file completeness at each stage gate. Sourced from DocuSign CLM.' .

ind:Tenant rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Tenant ;
    rdfs:label 'Tenant' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT master record for all tenant and prospect identities across commercial and residential portfolios. Captures legal name, entity type (B2B corporate vs B2C residential), tax identification, incorporation details, credit tier, CRM account linkage, property management system tenant code, onboarding status, and lifecycle stage (prospect, applicant, active tenant, former tenant). Serves as the authoritative golden record for every occupant and prospective occupant across the enterprise.' .

ind:TenantContact rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Tenant ;
    rdfs:label 'Tenant Contact' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual contact persons associated with a tenant profile — primary contacts, authorized signatories, emergency contacts, billing contacts, and property access contacts. Supports both B2B corporate tenant hierarchies (multiple contacts per corporate entity) and B2C residential occupants (household members). Stores full name, role, phone, email, preferred communication channel, and CRM contact linkage.' .

ind:CorporateEntity rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Tenant ;
    rdfs:label 'Corporate Entity' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for B2B corporate tenants capturing legal entity structure — parent company, subsidiaries, joint ventures, and affiliated entities. Stores DUNS number, SIC/NAICS industry code, annual revenue, employee headcount, publicly traded flag, stock ticker, credit rating agency scores, and corporate hierarchy linkage. Enables enterprise-wide exposure tracking across multiple leased premises for institutional and corporate occupiers.' .

ind:Household rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Tenant ;
    rdfs:label 'Household' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Residential household grouping entity linking multiple individual occupants (adults, dependents, co-signers) to a single residential tenancy. Captures household composition, combined income, household size, pet ownership, vehicle registrations, and HOA membership status. Supports B2C residential portfolio management and fair housing compliance tracking per HUD requirements.' .

ind:CreditProfile rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Tenant ;
    rdfs:label 'Credit Profile' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tenant credit and financial qualification record capturing credit bureau scores, credit check authorization date, debt-to-income ratio, income verification status, bankruptcy history, prior eviction flag, guarantor requirement flag, security deposit multiplier, and credit review expiry date. Sourced from third-party credit bureaus and stored as the authoritative credit qualification record per tenant for leasing underwriting decisions.' .

ind:TenantProspect rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Tenant ;
    rdfs:label 'Tenant Prospect' ;
    rdfs:comment 'CRM-linked prospect pipeline record for prospective tenants in the leasing funnel. Captures lead source, inquiry date, property of interest, unit type preference, desired move-in date, budget range (PSF or monthly), pipeline stage (inquiry, tour scheduled, application submitted, LOI issued, lease negotiation), assigned leasing agent, and conversion probability. Bridges brokerage activity and tenant onboarding.' .

ind:Application rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Tenant ;
    rdfs:label 'Application' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Formal tenancy application submitted by a prospect or existing tenant for a specific unit or premises. Captures application date, applicant type (individual, corporate, guarantor), requested GLA/NLA, proposed lease term, submitted financial documents checklist, application fee amount, application status (submitted, under review, approved, declined, withdrawn), decline reason code, and approval authority. Tracks the formal qualification workflow prior to lease execution.' .

ind:TenantOccupancy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Tenant ;
    rdfs:label 'Tenant Occupancy' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Active and historical occupancy record linking a tenant to a specific property unit or premises for a defined period. Captures occupancy start date, end date, occupancy type (primary, sublease, holdover, license), actual occupied area (SQF/SQM), certificate of occupancy reference, move-in and move-out inspection dates, key handover date, occupancy status, and vacate reason code. Serves as the SSOT for physical possession across the entire portfolio — both current and historical — distinct from the legal lease agreement owned by the lease domain. Supports tenant lifecycle analytics, re-leasing decisions, reference checks, and portfolio occupancy reporting.' .

ind:Guarantor rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Tenant ;
    rdfs:label 'Guarantor' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Guarantor record for tenants requiring a co-signer or financial guarantor on a lease — common in residential tenancies for students/first-time renters and for corporate tenants with insufficient credit history or foreign entities. Captures guarantor type (individual, corporate, institutional), legal name, tax ID, relationship to tenant, guaranteed amount or percentage of lease obligation, guarantee instrument type (personal guarantee, letter of credit, surety bond, cash deposit), guarantee effective and expiry dates, credit qualification status, and guarantor contact details. Supports lease underwriting, guarantee enforcement, and portfolio credit risk assessment.' .

ind:Interaction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Tenant ;
    rdfs:label 'Interaction' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Record of all tenant and prospect interactions — calls, emails, meetings, portal messages, site tours, and service escalations. Captures interaction date, channel, direction (inbound/outbound), subject, summary, outcome, follow-up required flag, assigned relationship manager, and linked prospect or active tenant. Supports tenant relationship management, CRM pipeline visibility, and communication audit trail.' .

ind:Notice rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Tenant ;
    rdfs:label 'Notice' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Formal notice record issued to or received from a tenant covering the full spectrum of landlord-tenant legal communications: notice to vacate, lease renewal notice, rent increase notice, cure/default notice, lease termination notice, HOA violation notice, and estoppel certificate requests. Captures notice type, direction (inbound/outbound), issue date, effective date, statutory response deadline, delivery method (certified mail, email, portal, in-person), delivery confirmation status, response received flag, and digital signature reference. Supports lease administration, statutory compliance with state/local notice period requirements, and litigation readiness.' .

ind:Document rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Tenant ;
    rdfs:label 'Document' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tenant document repository record tracking all documents associated with a tenant profile — identification documents, incorporation certificates, financial statements, tax returns, signed lease abstracts, LOIs, SNDA agreements, and digitally executed documents. Captures document type, document name, version, upload date, expiry date, storage reference, and document status (active, expired, superseded, archived). Supports lease administration, regulatory compliance, and tenant onboarding documentation requirements.' .

ind:ArrearsEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Tenant ;
    rdfs:label 'Arrears Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tenant rent arrears and delinquency event record capturing each instance of overdue rent, CAM charges, or other lease-obligated payments. Records amount overdue, days past due, arrears stage (first notice, second notice, demand letter, legal referral, eviction proceedings), collection actions taken, payment plan terms, cure date, and resolution status. Provides the tenant-facing delinquency lifecycle view for relationship managers, distinct from the finance domain\'s AR aging records, enabling coordinated collections strategy and tenant retention decisions.' .

ind:RetentionAction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Tenant ;
    rdfs:label 'Retention Action' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tenant retention and renewal campaign action record capturing proactive relationship management activities — lease renewal outreach, rent concession offers, TI allowance proposals, lease restructuring discussions, and escalation to senior asset management. Captures action type, action date, assigned relationship manager, offer details (free rent months, TI PSF, rent abatement), tenant response, and outcome (retained, lost, pending). Supports WALE management and portfolio retention strategy.' .

ind:CostCenter rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Cost Center' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master registry of cost centers used for financial allocation and reporting across the real estate portfolio. Each cost center maps to a property, department, or business unit and serves as the foundational dimension for GL posting, NOI statements, and OPEX/CAPEX tracking. Attributes include cost center code, name, type (property-level, corporate, departmental), responsible manager, active status, effective dates, hierarchy parent, and functional currency.' .

ind:ChartOfAccounts rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Chart Of Accounts' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Enterprise chart of accounts defining the full GL account hierarchy used across all properties and legal entities. Establishes the authoritative account structure for income, expense, asset, liability, and equity classifications. Supports FASB ASC 842 lease accounting and SOX-compliant financial controls. Attributes include account code, account name, account type (asset, liability, equity, revenue, expense), sub-type, normal balance, parent account, IFRS 16 mapping flag, and active status.' .

ind:LegalEntity rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Legal Entity' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master registry of all legal entities within the real estate enterprise — including property-owning SPEs, REITs, joint-venture entities, holding companies, and operating subsidiaries. Serves as the consolidation anchor for financial reporting and SOX compliance. Attributes include entity name, entity type (REIT, LLC, LP, JV), EIN/tax ID, jurisdiction, functional currency, consolidation method, parent entity, REIT election status, and SEC reporting flag.' .

ind:JournalEntry rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Journal Entry' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core GL transactional record capturing all financial postings across the real estate portfolio with embedded debit/credit line items. Each entry is a balanced posting event with line-level detail mapped to GL accounts, cost centers, and properties. Supports property-level P&L, NOI statements, CAM allocations, EBITDA roll-ups, and SOX audit trails. Sourced from Yardi Voyager and SAP S/4HANA. Attributes include journal entry number, posting date, period, document type, source system, approval status, reversal flag, and per-line: debit/credit indicator, amount, functional currency amount, GL account, cost center, property reference, profit center, segment, tax code, and line description.' .

ind:JournalEntryLine rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Journal Entry Line' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual debit or credit line items within a journal entry, each mapped to a GL account, cost center, and property. Provides the granular posting detail required for property-level NOI statements, CAM reconciliations, and OPEX/CAPEX allocations. Attributes include line number, debit/credit indicator, amount, functional currency amount, account code, cost center, property reference, profit center, segment, tax code, and line description.' .

ind:ApInvoice rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Ap Invoice' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Accounts payable records covering the full procure-to-pay cycle for vendor payments related to property operations, construction, maintenance, and corporate services. Captures vendor invoices and associated disbursements (check runs, ACH, wire transfers) from Yardi Voyager AP and SAP S/4HANA. Invoice attributes include invoice number, vendor ID, invoice date, due date, payment terms, gross amount, tax amount, net amount, currency, property/cost center allocation, approval status, PO reference, and source system. Payment attributes include payment number, payment date, payment method, bank account, payment amount, cleared date, void flag, and void date.' .

ind:ApPayment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Ap Payment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records of actual disbursements made to vendors against AP invoices, including check runs, ACH transfers, and wire payments. Tracks payment execution for property operating expenses, TI allowances, construction draws, and corporate payables. Attributes include payment number, payment date, payment method (check, ACH, wire), bank account, payment amount, currency, cleared date, void flag, void date, and associated invoice references.' .

ind:ArInvoice rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Ar Invoice' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Accounts receivable records covering the full order-to-cash cycle for tenant charges and cash receipts — rent billings, CAM reconciliations, percentage rent, TI reimbursements, and miscellaneous property income. Sourced from Yardi Voyager AR. Invoice attributes include invoice number, tenant reference, lease reference, property reference, invoice date, due date, billing period, charge type (base rent, CAM, percentage rent, parking, utility, late fee), gross amount, tax amount, net amount, currency, and aging bucket. Receipt attributes include receipt number, receipt date, payment method, bank deposit reference, amount received, applied amount, unapplied amount, and NSF flag. Supports EGI/PGI calculations and tenant receivable aging reports.' .

ind:ArReceipt rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Ar Receipt' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records of cash receipts and tenant payments applied against AR invoices, including rent payments, security deposit receipts, and miscellaneous income. Tracks EGI realization at the property level. Attributes include receipt number, receipt date, payment method, bank deposit reference, amount received, currency, applied amount, unapplied amount, tenant reference, property reference, and NSF flag.' .

ind:FinanceBudget rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Finance Budget' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Annual and multi-year operating and capital budgets at the property, cost center, and portfolio level with embedded line-item detail by GL account and period. Serves as the baseline for NOI variance analysis, OPEX/CAPEX planning, and investor reporting. Sourced from Yardi Voyager Budgeting and SAP S/4HANA. Attributes include budget name, type (operating, capital, reforecast), fiscal year, version, status, approval chain, and per-line: GL account, cost center, property reference, period, budgeted amount, prior year actual, variance amount, variance percentage, and line description.' .

ind:BudgetLine rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Budget Line' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Granular budget line items by GL account, cost center, and period within an approved budget. Enables property-level and portfolio-level variance analysis between actual and budgeted NOI, EGI, PGI, and OPEX. Attributes include budget line number, GL account, cost center, property reference, period, budgeted amount, prior year actual, variance amount, variance percentage, and line description.' .

ind:FinancialForecast rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Financial Forecast' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Rolling financial forecasts and reforecasts at the property and portfolio level, capturing projected NOI, EGI, PGI, OPEX, CAPEX, and EBITDA. Supports investor reporting, DSCR covenant monitoring, and Argus Enterprise cash flow model inputs. Attributes include forecast name, forecast type (rolling, annual, multi-year), fiscal year, forecast period, version, status, projected NOI, projected EGI, projected PGI, projected OPEX, projected CAPEX, DSCR projection, and prepared-by user.' .

ind:NoiStatement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Noi Statement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Property-level Net Operating Income statement capturing the full income waterfall — PGI, vacancy and credit loss, concessions, EGI, itemized operating expenses, and NOI — for a given reporting period. Serves as the authoritative financial performance record for each property and the primary input for CAP rate valuation, DSCR calculations, and investor reporting. Attributes include statement period, property reference, PGI, vacancy loss, concessions, EGI, operating expense categories, NOI, management fee, CAP rate applied, and reporting currency.' .

ind:FixedAsset rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Fixed Asset' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Fixed asset register for all capitalized real estate assets including buildings, land improvements, tenant improvements (TI), HVAC systems, and capital equipment. Supports CAPEX tracking, depreciation schedules, and FASB ASC 360 asset impairment testing. Sourced from Yardi Voyager Fixed Assets and SAP S/4HANA FA. Attributes include asset number, asset description, asset class, property reference, acquisition date, acquisition cost, useful life, depreciation method, accumulated depreciation, net book value, disposal date, and disposal proceeds.' .

ind:BankAccount rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Bank Account' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master registry of all corporate and property-level bank accounts used for cash management, rent collection, operating disbursements, and escrow. Supports cash position monitoring and bank reconciliation. Attributes include account number (masked), bank name, bank routing number, account type (operating, escrow, security deposit, reserve), currency, property or entity reference, account status, and signatory details.' .

ind:IntercompanyTransaction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Intercompany Transaction' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records of financial transactions between legal entities within the real estate enterprise — management fee allocations, intercompany loans, shared service cost allocations, equity contributions, and distribution payments. Critical for financial consolidation, elimination entries, and REIT distribution compliance. Attributes include transaction date, sending entity, receiving entity, transaction type, amount, currency, GL account, elimination flag, netting status, and approval status.' .

ind:DebtInstrument rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Debt Instrument' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master registry of all property-level and portfolio-level debt instruments — mortgages, construction loans, mezzanine debt, CMBS, and credit facilities — with embedded debt service payment history. Supports LTV monitoring, DSCR covenant tracking, amortization schedules, and lender reporting. Attributes include loan number, lender, loan type, original principal, outstanding balance, interest rate, rate type (fixed/variable), maturity date, LTV ratio, DSCR covenant threshold, collateral property reference, and per-payment: scheduled/actual principal and interest amounts, payment date, payment status, outstanding balance after payment, escrow amount, and late fees.' .

ind:DebtServicePayment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Debt Service Payment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records of scheduled and actual debt service payments (principal and interest) made against debt instruments. Supports DSCR calculations, cash flow modeling, and lender covenant reporting. Attributes include payment date, scheduled date, payment type (principal, interest, escrow), scheduled principal amount, scheduled interest amount, actual principal paid, actual interest paid, outstanding balance after payment, payment status, and late fee amount.' .

ind:FinancialPeriodClose rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Financial Period Close' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Fiscal calendar periods and month-end/year-end financial close management for each legal entity. Defines when GL postings are open or closed and tracks close process execution — task completion, sign-off milestones, and SOX control checkpoints. Ensures completeness of GL postings, AR/AP reconciliations, and intercompany eliminations before period lock. Attributes include fiscal year, period number, period name, start/end dates, period status (open, closed, locked), close type (monthly, quarterly, annual), target/actual close dates, outstanding task count, SOX sign-off flag, controller sign-off, and close timestamp.' .

ind:TaxProvision rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Tax Provision' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records of income tax provisions, property tax accruals, and deferred tax calculations at the entity and property level. Supports REIT distribution requirements, tax compliance filings, and FASB ASC 740 income tax accounting. Attributes include provision period, entity reference, property reference, tax type (income, property, transfer, sales), current tax expense, deferred tax asset, deferred tax liability, effective tax rate, provision status, and filing jurisdiction.' .

ind:LeaseAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Lease Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for every executed lease agreement across commercial and residential portfolios. Captures lease type (NNN, gross, modified gross, full-service, ground), commencement and expiration dates, base rent, rent escalation structure, security deposit terms, TI allowance, CAM obligations, permitted use, holdover provisions, and key lease abstract data (critical dates, exclusivity, co-tenancy, assignment/subletting rights, insurance requirements). Stores WALT/WALE metrics, ASC 842/IFRS 16 classification (operating vs. finance), right-of-use asset value, lease liability, and discount rate. Authoritative SSOT for all lease terms. Sourced from Yardi Voyager Lease Administration and MRI Lease Management modules. Links to property, tenant, and owner domains via FK.' .

ind:Loi rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Loi' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Letter of Intent record capturing pre-lease negotiation terms between landlord and prospective tenant. Stores proposed rent PSF, proposed lease term, TI allowance offer, free-rent period, exclusivity window, expiration date, deal status (draft, submitted, accepted, rejected, expired), and the responsible leasing agent. Sourced from Salesforce CRM deal pipeline and DocuSign CLM. Precedes the executed lease agreement in the lease lifecycle.' .

ind:Amendment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Amendment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records all executed amendments to a base lease agreement, including expansion options exercised, contraction events, rent modifications, term extensions, TI re-allowances, and permitted use changes. Tracks amendment number, effective date, amendment type, changed clauses with before/after values, revised rent, revised GLA/NLA, and DocuSign execution metadata. Each amendment is a distinct legal instrument modifying the parent agreement and triggers ASC 842 lease modification assessment. Sourced from Yardi Voyager and DocuSign CLM.' .

ind:RenewalOption rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Renewal Option' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines contractual renewal options embedded within a lease agreement, including option number, notice deadline, option term length, rent reset mechanism (fixed, CPI, fair market value), exercise status (unexercised, exercised, expired, waived), and exercise date. Enables WALT/WALE forecasting and lease expiry pipeline management. Sourced from Yardi Voyager lease abstract data.' .

ind:Termination rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Termination' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records lease termination events — early terminations, mutual surrenders, lease expirations, default-driven terminations, and holdover resolutions. Captures termination type, effective termination date, termination fee, notice date, cure period, holdover status at termination, final possession return date, and space condition at surrender. Triggers downstream AR settlement, security deposit return processing, and ASC 842 derecognition entries. Sourced from Yardi Voyager and DocuSign CLM.' .

ind:RentSchedule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Rent Schedule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Stores the full rent escalation schedule for a lease agreement, including each rent step period, effective start and end dates, base rent amount, rent PSF, escalation type (fixed step, CPI, percentage of sales), escalation rate or index, and free-rent periods. Enables accurate ASC 842 straight-line rent calculation and cash flow forecasting in Argus Enterprise. One agreement may have many rent schedule rows.' .

ind:CamSchedule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Cam Schedule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Annual CAM (Common Area Maintenance) reconciliation record comparing estimated CAM charges billed to tenants against actual operating expenses incurred. Captures reconciliation year, estimated CAM per lease, actual CAM allocated, gross-up factor, tenant pro-rata share, reconciliation variance, credit or additional charge due, and reconciliation status. Sourced from Yardi Voyager CAM module. Critical for NNN and modified gross lease portfolios.' .

ind:CamEstimate rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Cam Estimate' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Annual or periodic CAM estimate record establishing the budgeted CAM charge to be billed to a tenant for the upcoming period. Stores estimate year, estimated total operating expenses, tenant pro-rata share percentage, estimated monthly CAM charge, and the basis for the estimate (prior year actuals, budget). Sourced from Yardi Voyager budgeting module. Feeds monthly CAM billing prior to annual reconciliation.' .

ind:TiAllowance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Ti Allowance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tenant Improvement (TI) allowance record tracking the negotiated TI budget, disbursement schedule, approved spend, invoiced amounts, and remaining balance for a lease. Captures TI amount PSF, total TI budget, disbursement milestones, landlord work vs. tenant work scope, TI expiry date, and amortization terms if TI is structured as a loan. Sourced from Yardi Voyager and Procore project cost data.' .

ind:SndaAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Snda Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Subordination, Non-Disturbance and Attornment (SNDA) agreement record linking a lease to a specific lender or superior interest holder. Captures SNDA execution date, lender identity, loan reference number, non-disturbance protections granted, subordination acknowledgment, attornment obligations, SNDA expiration or release date, and DocuSign execution status. Required for institutional lenders, CMBS-financed properties, and mezzanine debt structures. Sourced from DocuSign CLM.' .

ind:Clause rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Clause' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Granular repository of individual lease clauses and special provisions extracted from executed agreements. Captures clause type (exclusivity, co-tenancy, kick-out, ROFO, ROFR, force majeure, assignment, subletting, audit rights), clause text summary, effective date, expiry date, and whether the clause is currently triggered or active. Enables portfolio-wide clause screening and risk management. Sourced from DocuSign CLM and Yardi Voyager lease abstract.' .

ind:LeaseDemisedSpace rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Lease Demised Space' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the specific demised premises (suite, floor, unit, or land parcel) covered by a lease agreement. Stores suite number, floor, GLA, NLA, usable area SQF/SQM, space type (office, retail, industrial, residential unit, storage), load factor, and space configuration. A single lease may cover multiple spaces (e.g., multi-floor tenants). Sourced from Yardi Voyager unit/space master. Bridges the lease domain to the property domain.' .

ind:Payment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Payment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records individual rent and charge payments received from tenants against a lease agreement. Captures payment date, payment type (base rent, CAM, TI reimbursement, security deposit, late fee, percentage rent), payment amount, payment method, applied period, outstanding balance, and delinquency flag. Sourced from Yardi Voyager Accounts Receivable module. This is the lease-domain AR transaction record tracking tenant payment performance; the finance domain GL owns the double-entry journal posting. Delineation: this product owns the tenant-facing billing/collection view; finance domain owns the enterprise accounting view.' .

ind:SecurityDeposit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Security Deposit' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks security deposit obligations and balances for each lease agreement. Captures deposit type (cash, letter of credit, surety bond), required deposit amount, held amount, letter of credit issuer and expiry, deposit reduction schedule, applied deductions, and return status upon lease termination. Sourced from Yardi Voyager. Critical for tenant credit risk management and lease-end settlement.' .

ind:PercentageRent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Percentage Rent' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages percentage rent (overage rent) obligations for retail leases where rent is partially based on tenant gross sales. Stores natural breakpoint, artificial breakpoint, percentage rate, reporting period, reported gross sales, calculated percentage rent due, and reconciliation status. Sourced from Yardi Voyager percentage rent module. Applicable to retail NNN and gross leases with sales-based rent components.' .

ind:AccountingEntry rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Accounting Entry' ;
    rdfs:comment 'ASC 842 / IFRS 16 lease accounting and disclosure compliance records. Captures initial recognition and subsequent measurement of right-of-use (ROU) assets and lease liabilities: lease classification (operating, finance), ROU asset value, accumulated amortization, lease liability balance, interest expense, principal reduction, straight-line rent expense, period-end carrying values, and aggregated disclosure data (maturity analysis, weighted-average remaining term, weighted-average discount rate, operating/finance/variable lease costs, sublease income). Supports FASB/IASB quarterly and annual disclosure requirements for public REITs. Sourced from Yardi Voyager lease accounting module and SAP S/4HANA.' .

ind:Disclosure rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Disclosure' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Aggregated ASC 842 / IFRS 16 disclosure data required for financial statement footnotes and SEC/regulatory filings. Captures maturity analysis of lease liabilities by year, weighted-average remaining lease term, weighted-average discount rate, operating lease cost, finance lease cost, variable lease cost, sublease income, and cash paid for lease liabilities. Sourced from Yardi Voyager and SAP S/4HANA. Supports quarterly and annual financial reporting for public REITs.' .

ind:Sublease rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Sublease' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records sublease arrangements where a primary tenant sublets all or part of their demised premises to a subtenant. Captures sublease commencement, expiration, sublet area SQF, sublease rent, subtenant identity, landlord consent date and status, sublease type (full assignment, partial sublease), profit/loss on sublease relative to head lease rent, and ASC 842 sublease classification (operating vs. finance for lessor accounting). Sourced from Yardi Voyager and DocuSign CLM. Distinct from the head lease agreement; linked to parent agreement via FK.' .

ind:GroundLease rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Ground Lease' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for ground lease arrangements where the landowner leases land to a developer or tenant who constructs improvements. Captures ground lease term (often 50–99 years), ground rent, rent escalation schedule, reversion rights, leasehold financing provisions, subordination terms (subordinated vs. unsubordinated), ground lessor/lessee identities, and improvement ownership at reversion. Sourced from Yardi Voyager and DocuSign CLM. Modeled as a distinct product due to unique legal structure, ultra-long duration, leasehold financing implications, and separate valuation methodology.' .

ind:Asset rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Asset' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master registry and single source of truth for every real estate asset the enterprise owns, manages, or brokers — the root anchor for the entire property domain. Each record represents one distinct property (commercial, residential, or mixed-use). Captures canonical identity: asset class (office, retail, industrial, multifamily, land, hospitality, self-storage), portfolio assignment, legal entity ownership, acquisition date, disposition date, asset status (active, disposed, under development, held for sale), GIS coordinates (latitude/longitude), legal description, APN (Assessor Parcel Number), FIPS code, market/submarket classification, and BIM model reference. All other property-domain products reference this entity as their parent.' .

ind:Building rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Building' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Physical building structure record associated with a real estate asset. One asset may contain multiple buildings (e.g., campus, mixed-use development). Captures building name, year built/renovated, floors above and below grade, total GLA/NLA (SQF and SQM), building class (A/B/C), construction type, structural system, building status (operational, under construction, demolished), COO number and date, fire suppression type, elevator count, parking stalls, and BIM reference. SSOT for building-level sustainability certifications (LEED level/date, BREEAM rating, ENERGY STAR score, WELL, FITWEL) with certifying body, certification number, expiration, and ESG reporting flags. SSOT for building amenity inventory (fitness, parking, F&B, conference, outdoor, technology, security) with capacity, hours, ADA compliance, and fee details. SSOT for floor plan records (as-built, current, proposed) with area breakdowns, load factors, and CAD/BIM file references. The comprehensive physical structure record and single source of truth for all building attributes, certifications, amenities, and floor plans in the portfolio.' .

ind:Parcel rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Parcel' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Land parcel record representing a legally defined unit of land as recorded by the county assessor. Captures APN (Assessor Parcel Number), legal description, lot size in acres and SQF, zoning classification code, zoning description, FAR (Floor Area Ratio) allowed, maximum building height, setback requirements, flood zone designation (FEMA), soil classification, environmental designation (Superfund, brownfield), GIS polygon boundary (WKT or GeoJSON), county, municipality, state, country, and parcel status (active, subdivided, merged). Serves as the authoritative land record underpinning title and ownership data.' .

ind:Unit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Unit' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Leasable or saleable unit within a building — apartment unit, office suite, retail bay, industrial bay, or storage unit. Captures unit number, floor number, unit type (studio, 1BR, 2BR, office suite, retail bay), rentable area in SQF and SQM, usable area, efficiency ratio, unit status (vacant, occupied, under renovation, offline), asking rent PSF, market rent PSF, unit configuration (open plan, private offices), ADA compliance flag, balcony/patio flag, view type, and date last renovated. The SSOT for all leasable space inventory within the portfolio.' .

ind:Space rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Space' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Sub-unit space or common area within a building, supporting multi-tenant floor configurations, co-working arrangements, and common area maintenance (CAM) allocations. Captures space number, space type (private office, conference room, common corridor, lobby, mechanical room, parking bay, storage), rentable area SQF, usable area SQF, load factor, CAM-eligible flag, space status (available, occupied, under build-out, offline), floor number, floor plan reference, and suite assignment. Enables precise GLA/NLA reconciliation, CAM charge calculations, and tenant improvement (TI) space planning across the portfolio.' .

ind:Address rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Address' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Standardized physical address record for properties, buildings, parcels, and units. Captures address line 1, address line 2, city, county, state/province, postal code, country, USPS standardization status, geocode latitude, geocode longitude, geocode accuracy level, MSA (Metropolitan Statistical Area) code, submarket name, neighborhood name, and address validation timestamp. Supports GIS integration, market analysis, and regulatory reporting. One asset or building may have multiple addresses (e.g., corner properties with multiple street frontages).' .

ind:PropertyOwnershipInterest rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Property Ownership Interest' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records the ownership interest structure for each real estate asset — capturing who owns what percentage of each property and under what legal structure. Supports complex ownership arrangements including joint ventures, tenancy-in-common (TIC), REIT structures, and fund ownership. Captures owner entity reference, ownership percentage, ownership type (fee simple, leasehold, ground lease, easement), legal entity name, legal entity type (LLC, LP, REIT, individual), acquisition date, disposition date, ownership status (active, transferred, dissolved), and title vesting language. Bridges the property domain to the owner domain.' .

ind:TitleRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Title Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Title, deed, and encumbrance registry for each real estate asset — the single source of truth for chain of title, all recorded encumbrances, and title insurance details. Stores deed type (warranty, quitclaim, grant, special warranty), deed book and page reference, recording date and number, county recorder jurisdiction, title company, policy number, policy type (ALTA owner, ALTA lender), policy amount, effective date, and title status (clear, encumbered, in dispute). SSOT for all encumbrances recorded against the asset: liens (mortgage lien, mechanics lien, tax lien), easements, deed restrictions, CC&Rs, rights-of-way, and ground lease encumbrances — with recording details, priority position, grantor/grantee, encumbrance amounts, maturity dates, release dates, and encumbrance status (active, released, expired, disputed). Critical for transaction due diligence, lender underwriting, SNDA management, and regulatory compliance.' .

ind:Inspection rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Inspection' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Physical property and building inspection records capturing scheduled and ad-hoc inspections for due diligence, regulatory compliance, insurance requirements, and condition assessment. Captures inspection type (property condition assessment, fire safety, elevator, HVAC, environmental Phase I/II, ADA compliance, roof, structural, seismic), inspection date, inspector name, inspector company, inspection status (scheduled, in progress, completed, failed), overall condition rating (1-5 scale), deficiency count, critical deficiency flag, estimated remediation cost, report document reference, next scheduled inspection date, and regulatory authority (OSHA, EPA, local fire marshal). Distinct from maintenance work orders — inspections are formal assessments that may trigger work orders but are not repair events themselves.' .

ind:OccupancyRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Occupancy Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Point-in-time and period occupancy snapshots for buildings and units — the transactional record capturing physical and economic occupancy rates for NOI calculations, investor reporting, and portfolio performance monitoring. Each record represents one reporting period (month or quarter) for one building or unit. Captures total leasable area SQF, occupied area SQF, vacant area SQF, physical occupancy rate, economic occupancy rate, occupied unit count, vacant unit count, units under notice, net absorption SQF, and data source system (Yardi Voyager, MRI, RealPage). Supports WALE/WALT calculations, REIT FFO/AFFO reporting, same-store NOI comparisons, rent roll reconciliation, and asset management dashboards.' .

ind:AssetHierarchy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Asset Hierarchy' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Hierarchical relationship structure organizing real estate assets into portfolios, funds, sub-portfolios, and geographic clusters for investment management, regulatory reporting, and operational roll-ups. Captures hierarchy node name, hierarchy node type (fund, portfolio, sub-portfolio, market, submarket, region, asset), parent node reference, hierarchy level number, effective date, end date, and hierarchy status (active, restructured, dissolved). Enables roll-up reporting from individual asset to fund level, supporting AUM calculations, GAV/NAV reporting, REIT segment disclosures (per SEC requirements), and geographic performance benchmarking.' .

ind:PropertyType rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Property Type' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Enterprise-wide property classification taxonomy organized as a self-referencing multi-level hierarchy. Level 1: asset class (commercial, residential, mixed-use, land, special-purpose). Level 2: sub-category (office, retail, industrial, hospitality, single-family, multifamily, condo). Level 3: quality tier / building class (Class A/B/C, trophy, institutional-grade, luxury, affordable). Level 4: space use type (office, retail, restaurant, medical, fitness, storage, parking). Level 5: construction method (wood frame, steel, concrete, masonry, modular). Level 6: amenity classification (building-level, unit-level, community). Each node carries applicable attributes: GLA applicability flags, zoning compatibility codes, fire resistance ratings (IBC Type I–V), ESG/LEED relevance indicators, CAM inclusion rules, TI allowance benchmarks, and measurement methodology (GLA/NLA/GFA). Aligned with RESO, CoStar, BOMA, and NAIOP standards. Referenced by property, lease, valuation, brokerage, development, and maintenance domains as the single source of truth for all property classification.' .

ind:LeaseType rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Lease Type' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Standardized classification of lease structures used across commercial and residential leasing — NNN (Triple Net), gross lease, modified gross, percentage lease, ground lease, sublease, and short-term/month-to-month. Defines rent calculation methodology, CAM/OpEx responsibility allocation, and applicable accounting treatment under ASC 842 / IFRS 16. Includes escalation method indicators (CPI, fixed-step, market reset) and renewal option classification. Serves as the authoritative lookup for lease administration across Yardi Voyager, MRI Software, and all operational domains requiring lease structure classification.' .

ind:TransactionType rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Transaction Type' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Controlled vocabulary for all real estate transaction categories — acquisition, disposition, 1031 exchange, REO sale, foreclosure, short sale, ground lease assignment, joint venture formation, and portfolio trade. Includes transaction sub-types, applicable regulatory reporting flags (SEC, HUD), and required documentation checklists per transaction category. Used by the transaction domain and brokerage domain as the authoritative classification source.' .

ind:GeographicHierarchy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Geographic Hierarchy' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Enterprise geographic hierarchy defining the spatial organization of the real estate portfolio — country, region, state/province, metropolitan statistical area (MSA), submarket, city, zip/postal code, and micro-location. Supports GIS-based portfolio analysis, market segmentation, and regulatory jurisdiction mapping. Aligns with CoStar submarket definitions and HUD geographic designations. Each node carries market tier classification (primary, secondary, tertiary) and applicable regulatory jurisdiction codes.' .

ind:MarketSegment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Market Segment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Standardized market segment and investment strategy classifications used for portfolio analysis, deal sourcing, and performance benchmarking. Commercial segments: core, core-plus, value-add, opportunistic, and distressed. Residential segments: affordable, workforce, market-rate, and luxury. Each segment defines risk profile descriptors, target IRR and CAP rate ranges, typical hold period benchmarks, leverage parameters, and exit strategy indicators. Referenced by investment, valuation, brokerage, and transaction domains for deal classification, portfolio allocation analysis, and investor reporting against NCREIF and INREV benchmarks.' .

ind:ZoningCode rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Zoning Code' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Authoritative registry of municipal and county zoning designations applicable to portfolio properties — residential (R1–R5), commercial (C1–C3), industrial (I1–I2), mixed-use (MU), agricultural (A), and special overlay districts. Captures FAR limits, height restrictions, permitted uses, conditional use requirements, and variance history. Sourced from municipal GIS databases and maintained for regulatory compliance and development feasibility analysis.' .

ind:CurrencyCode rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Currency Code' ;
    rdfs:comment 'ISO 4217 currency code registry supporting multi-currency financial operations across international real estate portfolios. Stores currency code, name, symbol, decimal precision, and active status. Includes exchange rate source reference and functional currency designation for REIT and fund-level financial consolidation under SAP S/4HANA. Supports AP/AR multi-currency processing in Yardi Voyager and financial reporting under FASB/IASB standards.' .

ind:Uom rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Uom' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Enterprise unit-of-measure registry for all measurement dimensions in real estate operations — area (SQF, SQM, GLA, NLA, GFA), linear (LF, LM), volume (CF, CM), weight (LB, KG), and rate-based measures (PSF/year, PSM/month). Defines conversion factors between imperial and metric systems, default UOM by geographic region, and applicable property types per measure. Critical for consistent rent calculations, valuation metrics, cross-border portfolio reporting, and regulatory area disclosures.' .

ind:IndustryClassification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Industry Classification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Standard industry classification codes for tenant and occupier categorization — NAICS (North American Industry Classification System), SIC (Standard Industrial Classification), and GICS (Global Industry Classification Standard). Used to classify tenant business types for portfolio diversification analysis, lease underwriting, and regulatory reporting. Supports retail tenant mix analysis (anchor vs. inline), office tenant sector concentration, and industrial occupier type tracking.' .

ind:AmenityType rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Amenity Type' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Controlled vocabulary for property and building amenities used in property marketing, tenant attraction, and asset valuation — fitness centers, rooftop terraces, parking structures, EV charging stations, conference facilities, concierge services, green spaces, and smart building features. Categorized by amenity class (building, unit-level, community), applicable property types, and ESG/LEED relevance flags. Used by property, lease, and brokerage domains for listing enrichment and comparable analysis.' .

ind:BuildingClass rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Building Class' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Standardized building quality classification system for commercial and residential assets — Class A, B, C for office and industrial; luxury, mid-market, affordable for residential; trophy, institutional-grade for investment-grade CRE. Defines classification criteria including age thresholds, construction quality standards, location grade, amenity requirements, and typical CAP rate ranges per class. Aligned with BOMA, NAIOP, and CoStar building class definitions.' .

ind:ConstructionType rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Construction Type' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference classification for building construction methods and structural systems — wood frame, steel frame, concrete (cast-in-place, precast, tilt-up), masonry, modular, and mixed construction. Includes fire resistance rating (Type I–V per IBC), structural system description, typical span capabilities, and applicable property type compatibility. Used by development, maintenance, and valuation domains for construction cost estimation, insurance underwriting, and building condition assessment.' .

ind:TenureType rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Tenure Type' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Classification of property ownership and tenure structures — freehold (fee simple), leasehold, condominium, cooperative (co-op), timeshare, life estate, easement, and air rights. Defines legal ownership characteristics, transferability constraints, financing eligibility (LTV limits, PMI applicability), and title insurance requirements per ALTA standards. Referenced by transaction, owner, and finance domains for deal structuring, title underwriting, and portfolio ownership analysis.' .

ind:DocumentType rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Document Type' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Enterprise document type registry classifying all real estate legal, operational, and financial documents — lease agreements, LOIs, SNDAs, estoppel certificates, PSAs, ALTA title commitments, Phase I/II environmental reports, certificates of occupancy, appraisal reports, loan documents, CMBS prospectuses, HOA governing documents, insurance certificates, and tax returns. Defines required signatories, regulatory retention periods (per SEC, SOX, state record-keeping laws), workflow routing rules, filing obligations, and document lifecycle states (draft, executed, expired, superseded). Serves as the authoritative lookup for document management, compliance, and audit trail across all operational domains.' .

ind:SpaceUseType rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Space Use Type' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Controlled vocabulary for leasable space use classifications within a building — office, retail, restaurant/food and beverage, medical/dental, fitness, storage, parking, rooftop, signage, and common area. Defines GLA/NLA measurement methodology per use type, applicable lease structures, TI allowance benchmarks, and CAM inclusion/exclusion rules. Used by lease, property, and brokerage domains for space inventory management and rent roll reporting.' .

ind:InvestmentVehicle rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Investment Vehicle' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference classification for real estate investment structures and legal vehicles — REIT (equity, mortgage, hybrid), private equity fund (open-end, closed-end), ODCE fund, value-add/opportunistic fund, joint venture (JV), separate account, CMBS, RMBS, DST (Delaware Statutory Trust), TIC (Tenants in Common), and 1031 exchange vehicle. Defines regulatory classification (SEC, FINRA, state blue sky), applicable tax treatment (pass-through, REIT distribution requirements, UBTI), investor eligibility requirements (accredited, qualified purchaser, institutional), minimum investment thresholds, and reporting standards (NCREIF, INREV, ANREV). Referenced by investment, transaction, owner, and finance domains for fund structuring, investor onboarding, and regulatory reporting.' .

ind:SustainabilityRating rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Sustainability Rating' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Registry of green building and sustainability certification schemes — LEED (Certified through Platinum), BREEAM (Pass through Outstanding), ENERGY STAR, WELL Building Standard, GRESB, Fitwel, and NABERS. Stores certification level definitions, scoring thresholds, applicable building types, certifying body, renewal cycle requirements, and ESG reporting framework alignment (GRI, SASB, TCFD). Referenced by property, development, and compliance domains for ESG portfolio tracking and investor reporting.' .

ind:Country rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Country' ;
    rdfs:comment 'ISO 3166-1 country registry supporting international real estate portfolio operations. Stores country code (alpha-2, alpha-3, numeric), country name, region/continent grouping, default currency, applicable regulatory frameworks (GDPR, local property law), and tax treaty status. Serves as the top-level node in the geographic hierarchy and is referenced by all domains requiring country-level jurisdiction identification.' .

ind:RegulatoryFramework rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Regulatory Framework' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Registry of regulatory and compliance frameworks governing real estate operations across all jurisdictions. Covers lease accounting (ASC 842, IFRS 16), financial reporting (SOX, SEC Regulation S-X), fair housing (HUD Fair Housing Act), environmental (EPA CERCLA, state brownfield programs), workplace safety (OSHA 29 CFR 1910), data privacy (GDPR, CCPA), accessibility (ADA), building codes (IBC, NFPA), and local ordinances (rent control, inclusionary zoning). Each framework record defines jurisdiction scope, effective date, sunset/renewal date, applicable business processes, required reporting cadence, penalty structure, responsible compliance owner, and cross-references to related frameworks. Serves as the authoritative framework registry for the compliance domain and all domains requiring regulatory context.' .

ind:DevProject rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Development ;
    rdfs:label 'Dev Project' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for each real estate development or major capital improvement project — ground-up construction, redevelopment, or large-scale CAPEX programs. Captures project name, type (ground-up, renovation, mixed-use), current phase (entitlement, design, construction, closeout), total GLA/NLA targets, zoning classification, project address, estimated and actual start/completion dates, total project budget, and project manager assignment. Includes closeout lifecycle attributes: COO number and issuance date, as-built document delivery date, warranty registration, final retainage release date, O&M manual submission status, and closeout package completion. Also records Procore project ID for source-system traceability. SSOT for all development project identity and full lifecycle from inception through closeout and handoff to asset management.' .

ind:Entitlement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Development ;
    rdfs:label 'Entitlement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks all entitlement activities and FAR compliance calculations for a development project — zoning approvals, variances, conditional use permits, environmental impact reviews, and planning commission decisions. Captures entitlement type, jurisdiction, application date, approval date, conditions of approval, and entitlement status. Includes FAR compliance detail: zoning district, base FAR allowance, bonus FAR mechanisms (affordable housing, open space, transit), total allowable FAR, proposed gross floor area, proposed FAR, as-built FAR, and FAR compliance status. Also records density limits, height restrictions, and the governing regulatory authority. Links to the parent dev_project. SSOT for all entitlement and zoning compliance data within the development domain.' .

ind:ConstructionPermit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Development ;
    rdfs:label 'Construction Permit' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records all building and construction permits associated with a development project — grading, foundation, structural, MEP, and final occupancy permits. Captures permit number, permit type, issuing authority (municipality/jurisdiction), application date, issuance date, expiration date, inspection status, COO linkage, fee amounts, and permit conditions or restrictions. SSOT for construction permit tracking within the development domain. Critical for regulatory compliance, inspection scheduling, and certificate of occupancy issuance workflow.' .

ind:ConstructionContract rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Development ;
    rdfs:label 'Construction Contract' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for each construction contract executed on a development project — GC agreements, subcontractor contracts, design-build contracts, and owner-architect agreements. Captures contract type (GMP, lump sum, cost-plus), contractor entity reference, contract value, executed date, substantial completion date, retainage percentage, bonding requirements, insurance certificates, change order allowance, and contract status. Sourced from DocuSign CLM and Procore.' .

ind:Contractor rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Development ;
    rdfs:label 'Contractor' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master registry of all contractors, subcontractors, and design professionals engaged on development projects — general contractors, specialty subcontractors, architects, engineers, and consultants. Captures company name, license number, license type, bonding capacity, insurance expiration, prequalification status, trade specialty, MBE/WBE/DBE certification, default contact, and historical performance rating. SSOT for contractor identity within the development domain. Supports prequalification workflows, insurance compliance tracking, and contractor performance evaluation across projects.' .

ind:ConstructionBudget rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Development ;
    rdfs:label 'Construction Budget' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks the approved CAPEX budget for each development project at both summary and cost-code-level detail. Summary level captures original budget, approved budget, current budget (including approved change orders), committed costs, actual costs to date, forecast at completion, and variance by category (hard costs, soft costs, land, financing, contingency). Line-item level captures individual cost codes (CSI division or custom WBS element), cost category, original and revised budget amounts, committed and actual spend, and remaining budget per line. Enables CAPEX draw schedule management, cost control, variance analysis, and investor reporting. Aligned with Procore budget module and SAP S/4HANA project systems for source-system integration.' .

ind:ChangeOrder rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Development ;
    rdfs:label 'Change Order' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records all change orders issued against construction contracts — owner-initiated changes, contractor-initiated scope modifications, unforeseen conditions, and design revisions. Captures change order number, originating contract, change type, description of scope change, cost impact, schedule impact (days), approval status, approval date, approving authority, and cumulative change order total against the contract. SSOT for construction change order tracking within the development domain. Critical for contract value management, budget variance analysis, and dispute documentation.' .

ind:DrawRequest rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Development ;
    rdfs:label 'Draw Request' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captures each CAPEX draw request (AIA G702/G703 pay application) submitted for payment against a construction contract, along with all associated lien waivers. Draw-level data: draw number, billing period, scheduled value, work completed to date, materials stored, total earned, retainage withheld, net payment due, lender approval status, title company review status, and disbursement date. Lien waiver detail per draw: waiver type (conditional/unconditional, progress/final), executing party (contractor or subcontractor), waiver amount, through-date, execution date, notarization status, and document storage reference. SSOT for construction payment applications and lien waiver compliance within the development domain. Critical for construction loan administration, CAPEX cash flow management, and lender/title requirements.' .

ind:Rfi rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Development ;
    rdfs:label 'Rfi' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks all Requests for Information (RFIs) raised during construction — contractor questions to the design team regarding drawings, specifications, or site conditions. Captures RFI number, subject, originating contractor, assigned design professional, question description, response text, response date, cost impact flag, schedule impact flag, status (open/answered/closed), and days to respond. SSOT for construction RFI tracking within the development domain. Critical for construction documentation, design clarification audit trail, and dispute resolution.' .

ind:Submittal rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Development ;
    rdfs:label 'Submittal' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records all construction submittals — shop drawings, product data, samples, and mock-ups submitted by contractors for design team review and approval. Captures submittal number, spec section, submittal type, submitting contractor, assigned reviewer, submission date, required response date, actual response date, review status (approved/approved as noted/revise and resubmit/rejected), revision number, and compliance notes. SSOT for construction submittal tracking within the development domain. Supports specification compliance verification and construction quality assurance.' .

ind:InspectionEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Development ;
    rdfs:label 'Inspection Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records all construction inspections conducted on a development project — municipal building inspections, third-party special inspections, lender inspections, and owner quality control inspections. Captures inspection type, inspection date, inspector name and affiliation, areas inspected, pass/fail result, deficiencies noted, corrective action required, re-inspection date, and final sign-off. Supports COO issuance tracking and OSHA compliance documentation.' .

ind:DesignDocument rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Development ;
    rdfs:label 'Design Document' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks all design documents and Building Information Models (BIM) associated with a development project — architectural drawings, engineering plans, specifications, geotechnical reports, survey documents, and BIM models (architectural, structural, MEP, civil, federated coordination). Core attributes: document number, document type, discipline, revision number, issue date, issue purpose (for construction, for permit, for record), author, approval status, and document management system reference. For BIM models, additionally captures authoring software (Revit, ArchiCAD), Level of Development (LOD), clash detection status, last coordination date, model manager, and BIM execution plan compliance. SSOT for all design documentation and BIM model registry within the development domain. Supports document control, digital twin linkage, and as-built record management.' .

ind:ProjectSchedule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Development ;
    rdfs:label 'Project Schedule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master schedule record for a development project — the baseline and current CPM (Critical Path Method) schedule with integrated milestone tracking. Schedule-level data: schedule version, baseline and current start/finish dates, total float, critical path activities count, schedule performance index (SPI), percent complete, last update date, and scheduling software reference (Primavera P6, MS Project). Milestone-level data: milestone name and type (entitlement approval, groundbreaking, foundation pour, topping out, substantial completion, COO issuance), planned date, forecast date, actual date, days variance, responsible party, predecessor relationships, and completion status. SSOT for project scheduling and milestone tracking within the development domain. Enables critical path analysis, schedule performance reporting, and investor milestone updates.' .

ind:EnvironmentalReview rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Development ;
    rdfs:label 'Environmental Review' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks environmental due diligence and compliance reviews for development projects — Phase I and Phase II Environmental Site Assessments (ESAs), NEPA reviews, wetlands delineations, and remediation plans. Captures review type, environmental consultant, assessment date, findings summary, recognized environmental conditions (RECs), remediation required flag, remediation cost estimate, regulatory agency, approval date, and clearance status. Supports EPA compliance and lender environmental requirements.' .

ind:RegulatoryObligation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Regulatory Obligation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master registry of all regulatory obligations applicable to the portfolio — federal, state, and local requirements including EPA environmental mandates, OSHA building safety codes, HUD fair housing rules, GDPR tenant data privacy, SEC REIT reporting, and municipal zoning compliance. Each obligation captures the governing body, regulation reference, jurisdiction, applicability scope (property type, asset class), effective dates, and renewal cadence. Serves as the authoritative catalog against which compliance activities are tracked.' .

ind:ComplianceProgram rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Compliance Program' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the enterprise compliance programs that govern how regulatory obligations are operationalized across the portfolio — e.g., EPA Phase I/II Environmental Program, OSHA Building Safety Program, HUD Fair Housing Program, GDPR Privacy Program, SOX Internal Controls Program, ESG Reporting Program, LEED/BREEAM Certification Program. Captures program owner, scope, policy framework references, program status, budget allocation, and the regulatory obligations it addresses. Acts as the organizing structure that groups requirements, assessments, training, and remediation activities into manageable compliance workstreams.' .

ind:Requirement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Requirement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Granular, actionable compliance requirements derived from regulatory obligations — specific tasks, controls, or submissions that must be completed (e.g., annual fire inspection, quarterly OSHA safety audit, annual HUD fair housing certification, GDPR data subject access request process, SEC 10-K REIT disclosure). Links to the parent regulatory obligation and compliance program. Captures requirement type, frequency, responsible party role, due date logic, and applicable property or jurisdiction scope.' .

ind:RegulatoryFiling rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Regulatory Filing' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of every regulatory filing submitted to a governing body — SEC REIT filings (10-K, 10-Q, 8-K), HUD fair housing reports, EPA environmental disclosures, OSHA incident reports, state and local permit applications, and municipal zoning filings. Captures filing type, governing body, jurisdiction, filing date, submission method, filing status (draft, submitted, accepted, rejected), reference number assigned by the regulator, and the property or portfolio scope covered.' .

ind:Assessment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Assessment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records the results of all compliance assessments, audits, inspections, and formal audit engagements conducted against properties or business units. Covers OSHA safety inspections, EPA environmental site assessments (Phase I/II), HUD fair housing audits, fire marshal inspections, building code compliance reviews, internal compliance audits, external financial audits, SOX audits, regulatory examinations, and third-party compliance audits. Captures assessment/audit type, assessor or auditing firm, scope (properties, business units, processes), assessment period, fieldwork dates, findings summary with severity classification, overall compliance status or audit opinion, report issuance date, and remediation requirements. Serves as the single master log of all formal compliance evaluation activities.' .

ind:RemediationAction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Remediation Action' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks corrective and preventive actions (CAPAs) required to resolve compliance assessment findings, regulatory violations, and enforcement actions. Each action captures the triggering event (assessment finding or violation), action description, responsible party, target and actual completion dates, estimated remediation cost, status (open, in-progress, completed, verified), and verification method. Supports OSHA corrective action plans, EPA remediation programs, HUD consent decree actions, SEC comment letter responses, and internal audit follow-up workflows. After merging assessment_finding into assessment, remediation actions link directly to the parent assessment or violation.' .

ind:OshaIncident rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Osha Incident' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records OSHA-reportable workplace safety incidents occurring at managed properties — injuries, illnesses, near-misses, and fatalities involving employees, contractors, or tenants. Captures incident type, OSHA recordability classification (300 log, 300A summary), date and time, location within property, persons involved, root cause analysis, OSHA case number, days away from work, and regulatory reporting status. Supports OSHA 300/300A log maintenance and mandatory incident reporting to OSHA.' .

ind:FairHousingRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Fair Housing Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks HUD fair housing compliance activities across residential and commercial leasing operations — fair housing training completions, accommodation requests (ADA/FHA), discrimination complaints received, investigation outcomes, and HUD audit responses. Captures protected class categories involved, complaint type, resolution status, settlement terms if applicable, and HUD case reference numbers. Supports compliance with the Fair Housing Act, Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA), and Equal Credit Opportunity Act (ECOA).' .

ind:PrivacyRequest rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Privacy Request' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages data subject rights requests under GDPR, CCPA, and other privacy regulations from tenants, prospects, employees, and other individuals. Covers subject access requests (SARs), right to erasure, data portability, consent withdrawals, objection to processing, and opt-out of sale (CCPA). Also serves as the registry for GDPR Article 30 Records of Processing Activities (RoPA) — documenting processing purposes, legal bases, data categories, retention periods, third-party processors, and cross-border transfer mechanisms. Captures request type, requestor identity, date received, response deadline, processing status, response date, and outcome. Supports GDPR Articles 15-22 and 30 compliance, CCPA consumer rights, and tenant data privacy obligations.' .

ind:EsgMetric rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Esg Metric' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captures ESG (Environmental, Social, and Governance) performance metrics at the property and portfolio level for investor reporting and regulatory disclosure. Environmental metrics include energy consumption (kWh), water usage, GHG emissions (Scope 1/2/3 in CO2e), waste diversion rates, and renewable energy percentage. Social metrics cover affordable housing units, community investment, and tenant satisfaction. Governance metrics track board diversity, ethics violations, and anti-corruption measures. Each metric record captures the reporting period, measurement methodology, data source, and verification status. Supports ESG reporting frameworks (GRI, SASB, TCFD, GRESB) and REIT investor ESG disclosure requirements.' .

ind:GreenCertification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Green Certification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for green building certifications obtained or pursued for properties — LEED (Leadership in Energy and Environmental Design), BREEAM (Building Research Establishment Environmental Assessment Method), ENERGY STAR, WELL Building Standard, and Fitwel certifications. Captures certification type, certifying body (USGBC, BRE, EPA), certification level (LEED Platinum/Gold/Silver/Certified), certification date, expiry date, points scored, prerequisites met, and renewal requirements. Supports ESG reporting and green lease obligations.' .

ind:Permit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Permit' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master registry of all permits required and obtained for properties — building permits, certificates of occupancy (COO), environmental permits, fire safety permits, elevator operating permits, demolition permits, and zoning variances. Captures permit type, issuing authority, jurisdiction, permit number, issue date, expiry date, renewal requirements, permit conditions, inspection history, and current status (active, expired, pending renewal, revoked). Critical for development, operations, and disposition compliance. Includes inspection records associated with permit issuance and renewal.' .

ind:SoxControl rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Sox Control' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Documents SOX (Sarbanes-Oxley Act) internal controls and their testing history for publicly traded REITs. Captures control definitions (control ID, objective, type — preventive/detective, owner, frequency) and test execution records (tester identity, test approach — inquiry/observation/inspection/re-performance, sample size, exceptions, test conclusion, sign-off status). Covers financial reporting controls, IT general controls (ITGCs), and entity-level controls. Each control record maintains the full testing history including the most recent test date, result (effective/ineffective), and any remediation status for identified deficiencies. Supports SOX Section 302 certifications, Section 404 management assessments, and external auditor reliance testing for SEC-reporting REITs.' .

ind:Violation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Violation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records confirmed regulatory violations, non-compliance events, enforcement actions, and OSHA-reportable workplace safety incidents across all compliance programs. Covers EPA notices of violation, OSHA citations and recordable incidents (injuries, illnesses, near-misses, fatalities with 300/300A log classification), HUD enforcement actions, SEC comment letters, building code violations, and zoning violations. Captures violation/incident type, regulatory body, citation reference, date, severity (willful, serious, other-than-serious, de minimis), OSHA recordability classification, days away from work, root cause analysis, penalty amount assessed, contest status, and resolution outcome. Drives remediation workflows, regulatory response management, and mandatory incident reporting.' .

ind:ComplianceTraining rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Compliance Training' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks mandatory compliance training programs and completion records for employees, property managers, leasing agents, and contractors — fair housing training, OSHA safety training, GDPR data privacy training, anti-money laundering (AML) training, ethics and code of conduct training, and ESG awareness training. Captures training program name, regulatory requirement driving it, delivery method, completion date, expiry date, pass/fail status, and training provider. Supports HUD, OSHA, and GDPR training mandate compliance.' .

ind:AuditEngagement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Audit Engagement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records formal internal and external audit engagements conducted across the portfolio — internal audit reviews, external financial audits, SOX audits, regulatory examinations, and third-party compliance audits. Captures audit type, auditing firm or internal audit team, audit scope (properties, business units, processes), audit period, fieldwork start and end dates, report issuance date, overall audit opinion, and number of findings by severity. Serves as the master log of all formal audit activities.' .

ind:Jurisdiction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Jurisdiction' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference master for all regulatory jurisdictions applicable to the real estate portfolio — federal agencies (EPA, OSHA, HUD, SEC, CFPB), state regulatory bodies, county authorities, and municipal/city agencies. Each jurisdiction record captures the jurisdiction level (federal, state, county, city, special district), jurisdiction name, governing body, geographic boundaries, applicable regulatory frameworks, key contact information, and filing portal details. Serves as the authoritative lookup for multi-jurisdictional compliance mapping and is referenced by obligations, filings, permits, and violations to assign jurisdictional scope.' .

ind:Fund rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Investment ;
    rdfs:label 'Fund' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master registry of real estate investment funds, REITs, and pooled investment vehicles. Captures fund name, type (open-end, closed-end, REIT, partnership, CMBS/RMBS trust), domicile jurisdiction, base currency, target and actual AUM, inception date, fund status, investment strategy (core, core-plus, value-add, opportunistic), target return metrics (IRR, equity multiple), fee terms (management fee rate, carried interest, preferred return hurdle, fee basis, fee cap, fee waiver conditions), fund term and extension options, GP entity, regulatory classification, ESG mandate, and investment mandate parameters (target property types, geographies, leverage range, deal size range, concentration limits). SSOT for fund identity, strategy, terms, fee structures, and mandate parameters.' .

ind:Portfolio rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Investment ;
    rdfs:label 'Portfolio' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for an investment portfolio — a named collection of real estate assets managed under a unified strategy. Captures portfolio name, portfolio type (core, diversified, sector-specific), associated fund, asset manager (AM), benchmark index, target GAV, target NAV, target NOI, geographic focus, property type focus, WALT target, WALE target, portfolio inception date, reporting currency, consolidation entity, and portfolio status. Serves as the SSOT for portfolio-level identity and strategy. Sourced from MRI Software and Argus Enterprise.' .

ind:Vehicle rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Investment ;
    rdfs:label 'Vehicle' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the legal and structural wrapper through which capital is deployed — including LLCs, LPs, joint ventures, co-investment structures, CMBS/RMBS trusts, and separately managed accounts (SMAs). Captures vehicle name, vehicle type, legal entity identifier (LEI), jurisdiction of formation, GP/LP split, ownership percentage, tax classification (pass-through, REIT, C-Corp), regulatory filing status, co-investment flag, and relationship to parent fund. Distinct from fund (the investment product offered to investors) — this is the legal holding structure through which fund capital flows.' .

ind:Investor rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Investment ;
    rdfs:label 'Investor' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for institutional and individual investor identities participating in real estate funds and portfolios. Captures investor legal name, investor type (institutional, HNWI, family office, pension fund, sovereign wealth fund, endowment, retail), KYC/AML status, accreditation status, domicile country, tax identification, preferred currency, investor tier, relationship manager, onboarding date, and investor status. Distinct from the owner domain (which tracks property ownership) — this entity tracks capital contributors to investment vehicles.' .

ind:Commitment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Investment ;
    rdfs:label 'Commitment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records the formal capital commitment made by an investor to a fund or investment vehicle. Captures commitment amount, commitment currency, commitment date, commitment status (pending, executed, funded, defaulted), subscription agreement reference, capital call schedule, total called capital, uncalled capital (dry powder), total distributed capital, and co-investment flag. Tracks the lifecycle from LOI through full deployment. Sourced from MRI Software Investment Management.' .

ind:CapitalCall rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Investment ;
    rdfs:label 'Capital Call' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of each capital call notice issued to investors, requesting funded capital from committed but uncalled amounts. Captures call number, call date, call amount, call percentage of commitment, due date, purpose (acquisition, capex, fees, reserves), funding status, actual funded amount, shortfall amount, default flag, and wire transfer reference. Linked to commitment and fund. Supports LP capital account reconciliation and fund cash management. Sourced from MRI Software.' .

ind:InvestmentDistribution rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Investment ;
    rdfs:label 'Investment Distribution' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records capital and income distributions made from a fund or investment vehicle to investors. Captures distribution date, distribution type (return of capital, income, capital gain, preferred return, carried interest), gross distribution amount, withholding tax amount, net distribution amount, distribution per unit/share, distribution frequency, reinvestment election flag, and payment method. Supports FFO/AFFO reporting and investor waterfall calculations. Sourced from MRI Software and Yardi Voyager.' .

ind:PortfolioAsset rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Investment ;
    rdfs:label 'Portfolio Asset' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Association entity linking a property asset to an investment portfolio, capturing the investment-specific attributes of that holding. Records acquisition cost, acquisition date, current book value, appraised value, ownership percentage, hold strategy (core hold, value-add, disposition target), target exit date, allocated debt, equity invested, unrealized gain/loss, and asset manager assignment. Distinct from the property domain master record — this entity captures the investment lens on each asset within a portfolio context. Cross-references property_id from the property domain.' .

ind:FundPerformance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Investment ;
    rdfs:label 'Fund Performance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Period-level investment performance and valuation record for a fund — the operational SSOT for how a fund performed and was valued in a given measurement period. Captures period dates, period type (quarterly, annual, trailing-12, since-inception), gross/net IRR, equity multiple (MOIC), NPV, DPI, RVPI, TVPI, TWR, MWR, benchmark return, alpha, GAV (sum of appraised values), NAV (GAV minus liabilities), NAV per unit/share, units outstanding, premium/discount to NAV, AUM, total revenue, NOI, FFO, AFFO, OPEX, CAPEX, leverage ratio, NAV calculation methodology, auditor sign-off status, and period status (open, closed, audited). Supports REIT reporting, investor redemption pricing, SEC filings, and ILPA reporting standards. Sourced from Argus Enterprise and MRI Software.' .

ind:AssetPerformance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Investment ;
    rdfs:label 'Asset Performance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Period-level performance, valuation, and DCF modeling record for an individual portfolio asset. Captures actual results (NOI, EGI, PGI, vacancy rate, CAP rate, cash-on-cash return, unlevered/levered IRR, NPV, DSCR, LTV, total return, OPEX PSF, revenue PSF, occupancy rate, WALT, WALE) and DCF model parameters (model version, discount rate, hold period, projected NOI by year, projected growth rates, exit CAP rate, terminal value, sensitivity scenario). Enables asset-level attribution, scenario analysis, and roll-up to portfolio and fund performance. SSOT for investment-oriented asset analytics. Sourced from Argus Enterprise and Yardi Voyager.' .

ind:DebtFacility rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Investment ;
    rdfs:label 'Debt Facility' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for debt financing instruments secured against investment assets or portfolios — mortgage loans, construction loans, bridge loans, mezzanine debt, CMBS/RMBS, and credit facilities. Captures lender, facility type, principal amounts, interest rate terms, maturity, amortization, LTV, collateral references, recourse type, facility status, and full covenant details: covenant type (LTV, DSCR, occupancy, NOI, debt yield), threshold values, measurement frequency, last measured values, compliance status (compliant, waiver, breach), cure periods, and lender notification requirements. SSOT for investment-level debt instruments and covenant compliance monitoring.' .

ind:DebtCovenant rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Investment ;
    rdfs:label 'Debt Covenant' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks financial and operational covenants associated with debt facilities. Captures covenant type (LTV, DSCR, occupancy, NOI, debt yield), covenant threshold value, measurement frequency, last measured value, last measurement date, covenant status (compliant, waiver, breach), cure period, and lender notification requirement. Enables proactive covenant compliance monitoring across the debt portfolio. Sourced from MRI Software and SAP S/4HANA.' .

ind:InvestmentDeal rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Investment ;
    rdfs:label 'Investment Deal' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks prospective investment opportunities from initial sourcing through IC approval and closing or rejection. Captures deal name, deal type (acquisition, disposition, recapitalization, JV formation), property type, market/submarket, asking price, underwritten value, target CAP rate, target IRR, deal stage (sourced, LOI, due diligence, IC review, under contract, closed, dead), deal source (broker, off-market, auction), assigned AM, LOI date, contract date, projected close date, IC memo details (recommendation, underwritten equity/debt, key risks, conditions of approval, IC decision, approving members, approval date), and deal status. SSOT for the investment pipeline and IC governance audit trail.' .

ind:IcMemo rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Investment ;
    rdfs:label 'Ic Memo' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records Investment Committee (IC) approval memos and decisions for proposed investments, dispositions, and major capital events. Captures memo date, deal reference, recommendation type (approve, reject, approve with conditions), requested equity, requested debt, underwritten IRR, underwritten equity multiple, key risks identified, conditions of approval, IC meeting date, IC decision, approving members, and final approval status. Supports governance and audit trail for investment decisions.' .

ind:Waterfall rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Investment ;
    rdfs:label 'Waterfall' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the economic waterfall and profit-sharing structure for a fund or investment vehicle — the rules governing how cash flows are split between LP investors and the GP. Captures waterfall type (American, European), preferred return (hurdle rate), GP catch-up percentage, carried interest rate, clawback provision flag, distribution tiers (tier 1 through N), tier threshold amounts, LP split per tier, GP split per tier, and effective date. Sourced from fund legal documents and MRI Software.' .

ind:CapitalAccount rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Investment ;
    rdfs:label 'Capital Account' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Periodic investor capital account statement summarizing each investor\'s position in a fund. Captures statement period, beginning capital account balance, capital contributions in period, distributions in period, allocated income/loss, management fees charged, carried interest allocated, ending capital account balance, ownership percentage, unrealized gain/loss, and cumulative IRR since inception. Supports LP reporting obligations and ILPA transparency standards. SSOT for investor-level fund position reporting.' .

ind:FeeStructure rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Investment ;
    rdfs:label 'Fee Structure' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the fee structures applicable to a fund or investment vehicle — management fees, acquisition fees, disposition fees, asset management fees, and performance fees. Captures fee type, fee basis (AUM, committed capital, invested capital, GAV, NAV), fee rate, fee calculation method, fee frequency, fee cap, fee waiver conditions, and effective date range. Supports accurate fee accrual and investor reporting. Sourced from fund legal documents and MRI Software.' .

ind:Appraisal rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Valuation ;
    rdfs:label 'Appraisal' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for a formal property appraisal engagement, its deliverable report(s), and status lifecycle. Captures the appraisal order, assigned certified appraiser (MAI, SRA, AI-GRS), appraisal type (full, limited, desktop, drive-by), purpose (financing, disposition, insurance, tax appeal, portfolio review, litigation), USPAP/IVSC-compliant methodology, engagement and report delivery dates, status lifecycle (ordered → in-progress → review → completed/rejected), concluded market value, value date, report format (URAR, narrative, restricted, summary), value type (market, investment, liquidation, insurable), report version (as-is, as-stabilized, as-complete), engagement letter reference, fee, turnaround SLA, and Argus Enterprise model ID where applicable. SSOT for all formal appraisal engagements and their output reports across the portfolio.' .

ind:Appraiser rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Valuation ;
    rdfs:label 'Appraiser' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master registry of certified appraisers and valuation professionals engaged by the firm. Stores Appraisal Institute designation (MAI, SRA, AI-GRS, AI-RRS), state license number, license expiration date, E&O insurance details, firm affiliation, geographic coverage areas, specialization (commercial, residential, industrial, land), IVSC membership flag, and engagement history summary. Distinct from the workforce domain employee record — this covers both internal staff appraisers and external fee appraisers.' .

ind:AppraisalReport rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Valuation ;
    rdfs:label 'Appraisal Report' ;
    rdfs:comment 'The formal deliverable output of an appraisal engagement. Stores report format (URAR, narrative, restricted, summary), concluded market value, value date (effective date of value), report date, value type (market value, investment value, liquidation value, insurable value), IVSC standard applied, report file reference (DocuSign CLM document ID), review status, and reviewer sign-off. One appraisal engagement may produce one or more reports (e.g., as-is vs. as-stabilized).' .

ind:Bpo rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Valuation ;
    rdfs:label 'Bpo' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Broker Price Opinion record capturing informal property value estimates prepared by licensed real estate brokers. Stores BPO type (drive-by, interior, desktop), requesting party, intended use, broker license number, opinion of value (point estimate and low/high range), effective date, market conditions narrative, days-on-market estimate, recommended list price, basis for opinion, engagement fee, turnaround SLA, requester reference, and comparable evidence references. Used for quick portfolio valuations, REO pricing, pre-listing assessments, and lender loss mitigation where a full USPAP appraisal is not required.' .

ind:Cma rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Valuation ;
    rdfs:label 'Cma' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Comparative Market Analysis record used by brokers and agents to estimate property value based on recent comparable sales and active listings. Stores subject property reference, analysis date, analyst (broker/agent), concluded value range, number of comparables used, market trend assessment (appreciating, stable, declining), absorption rate, average PSF of comparables, recommended pricing strategy, and engagement context. Distinct from BPO (less formal, agent-prepared, not broker-licensed requirement) and from full appraisal (not USPAP-compliant). Self-contained engagement record used primarily for listing price recommendations and seller consultations.' .

ind:ComparableSale rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Valuation ;
    rdfs:label 'Comparable Sale' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual comparable sale (comp) record used as evidence in appraisals, BPOs, and CMAs. Stores comp property address, sale date, sale price, price PSF, GLA/NLA, property type, year built, condition, location adjustments, physical adjustments, time adjustments, adjusted sale price, data source (CoStar, MLS, public record), and verification status. Supports the sales comparison approach in USPAP/IVSC-compliant valuations. Sourced from CoStar Suite and MLS data feeds.' .

ind:ComparableLease rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Valuation ;
    rdfs:label 'Comparable Lease' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Comparable lease transaction record used as market evidence in income capitalization and rent analysis. Stores comp property address, tenant name, lease execution date, lease commencement date, lease term (months), base rent PSF, rent type (NNN, gross, modified gross), TI allowance PSF, free rent period, lease size (SQF/SQM), property class, submarket, data source (CoStar, MLS, direct), and verification status. Supports market rent conclusions in income approach valuations.' .

ind:Approach rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Valuation ;
    rdfs:label 'Approach' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Valuation approach model record capturing the quantitative analysis for income capitalization and cost approach methodologies. For income capitalization: stores PGI, vacancy/credit loss rate, EGI, total OPEX, NOI, CAP rate, direct capitalization value, terminal CAP rate, discount rate, hold period, IRR/NPV outputs, and concluded market rent inputs. For cost approach: stores land value, replacement cost new (RCN), depreciation components (physical, functional, external obsolescence), depreciated cost of improvements, effective age, economic life, and cost index source (Marshall & Swift, RSMeans). Includes approach type discriminator (direct_cap, DCF, cost, sales_comparison, GRM) and approach weight in final reconciliation. Supports IVSC IVS 105 compliance. After merge with cost_approach, this is the unified approach model for all valuation methodologies.' .

ind:CostApproach rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Valuation ;
    rdfs:label 'Cost Approach' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Cost approach valuation model record capturing land value, replacement cost new (RCN), depreciation components (physical deterioration, functional obsolescence, external obsolescence), depreciated cost of improvements, and concluded value via cost approach. Stores cost estimator reference, Marshall & Swift or RSMeans cost index used, effective age, economic life, remaining economic life, and land-to-value ratio. Used primarily for special-use properties, insurance valuations, and new construction assessments.' .

ind:DcfModel rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Valuation ;
    rdfs:label 'Dcf Model' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Discounted Cash Flow model record linked to an Argus Enterprise model file. Stores Argus model ID, model version, hold period start and end dates, annual cash flow projections (year 1–10+), reversion/terminal value, discount rate (IRR target), NPV at various discount rates, levered vs. unlevered IRR, equity multiple, DSCR per period, LTV at acquisition, and model assumptions narrative. Serves as the quantitative backbone for investment-grade valuations and acquisition underwriting.' .

ind:CapRateBenchmark rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Valuation ;
    rdfs:label 'Cap Rate Benchmark' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Market CAP rate benchmark record by property type, submarket, and asset class sourced from industry surveys. Stores survey date, property type (office, retail, industrial, multifamily, hotel, data center), submarket/MSA, asset class (Class A/B/C), CAP rate range (low, mid, high), source (CoStar, CBRE, JLL, Cushman & Wakefield, NCREIF, PwC/Korpacz), survey methodology, sample size, and trend direction (compressing, stable, expanding). Used to validate appraiser CAP rate selections, support portfolio-level NAV/GAV calculations, and provide market context for investment committee presentations.' .

ind:NavCalculation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Valuation ;
    rdfs:label 'Nav Calculation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Net Asset Value (NAV) and Gross Asset Value (GAV) calculation record at the portfolio or fund level. Stores calculation date, portfolio/fund reference, total GAV (sum of market values), total debt outstanding, NAV (GAV minus debt), NAV per unit/share, AFFO adjustment, FFO, methodology (direct capitalization, DCF, third-party appraisal blend), number of properties included, and calculation preparer. Supports REIT financial reporting (SEC), investor reporting, and ASC 820 fair value disclosures.' .

ind:AppraisalReview rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Valuation ;
    rdfs:label 'Appraisal Review' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Formal appraisal review record capturing the desk review or field review of an appraisal report. Stores review type (desk, field, technical), reviewer credentials, review date, original appraisal reference, review conclusions (agree, disagree, conditional), value opinion of reviewer (if field review), deficiencies identified, USPAP Standard 3 compliance flag, and final disposition (accepted, rejected, revision required). Required for lender compliance, CMBS underwriting, and internal quality control.' .

ind:ValueHistory rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Valuation ;
    rdfs:label 'Value History' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Historical valuation record tracking all concluded values for a property over time. Stores property reference, valuation date, concluded value, value type (market value, assessed value, insurance value, book value, investment value), valuation method used, source discriminator (appraisal, BPO, CMA, internal desk review, tax assessment, automated valuation model), appraiser/analyst reference, confidence level, and financial reporting period association. Enables trend analysis, supports ASC 820 fair value hierarchy disclosures (Level 1/2/3), and provides the audit trail for REIT portfolio reporting and investor NAV reconciliation.' .

ind:TaxAssessment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Valuation ;
    rdfs:label 'Tax Assessment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Property tax assessment record capturing the assessed value assigned by the taxing authority for ad valorem tax purposes. Stores assessment year, assessed land value, assessed improvement value, total assessed value, assessment ratio, effective tax rate, annual tax liability, taxing jurisdiction, assessment notice date, appeal deadline, and appeal status. Distinct from market value appraisals — assessed value often differs materially from market value and drives property tax expense (a key OPEX component in NOI calculations).' .

ind:TaxAppeal rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Valuation ;
    rdfs:label 'Tax Appeal' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Property tax appeal record tracking formal challenges to assessed values filed with taxing authorities or assessment appeal boards. Stores appeal filing date, appeal type (informal, formal, judicial), grounds for appeal (overassessment, unequal assessment, exemption), opinion of value submitted, hearing date, settlement date, original assessed value, appealed value, settled/adjudicated value, tax savings achieved, legal counsel reference, and appeal status. Supports OPEX management and NOI optimization.' .

ind:Employee rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Employee' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record and Single Source of Truth (SSOT) for all real estate workforce personnel including property managers, asset managers, brokers, leasing agents, construction staff, facility operations staff, and corporate employees. Sourced from ADP Workforce Now. Captures legal name, preferred name, employee number, employment type (full-time, part-time, contractor), employment status (active, terminated, on-leave), hire date, termination date, rehire eligibility, job title, department, cost center, work location (property, regional office, corporate HQ), manager hierarchy, FLSA classification, EEO category, and HR system identifiers. Links to position for role assignment and org_unit for departmental membership.' .

ind:Position rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Position' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Authorized headcount positions and standardized job definitions within the organizational structure of the real estate enterprise. Captures position code, title, department, division, job family (Property Management, Brokerage, Development, Finance, Operations), job level/grade, FLSA classification, budgeted FTE, filled vs vacant status, reporting position, work location type, effective dates, required education, required experience, required licenses/certifications (e.g., broker license, appraiser credential, LEED certification), key responsibilities, compensation band reference, and competency frameworks. Supports workforce planning, headcount budgeting, org design, and serves as the template catalog for all recognized roles. A position may be vacant or filled by multiple employees over time. Sourced from ADP Workforce Now HCM module.' .

ind:JobProfile rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Job Profile' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Standardized job definitions and competency frameworks used across the real estate enterprise. Defines job code, job title, job family (e.g., Property Management, Brokerage, Development, Finance, Operations), job level, FLSA classification, required education, required experience, required licenses/certifications (e.g., real estate broker license, appraiser credential, LEED certification), key responsibilities, and compensation band reference. Serves as the catalog of all recognized roles and is the template from which positions are created. Sourced from ADP Workforce Now HCM module.' .

ind:OrgUnit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Org Unit' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Organizational hierarchy units and workforce planning data for the real estate enterprise. Org structure captures org unit code, name, type (division, department, team, cost center), parent org unit (for hierarchy traversal), responsible executive, GL cost center code, physical location, and effective dates. Workforce planning captures budgeted headcount (FTE) by planning period, actual filled headcount, open requisition count, planned hires and attrition, budgeted vs actual labor cost, variance, succession planning data for critical roles (successor candidates, readiness levels, development gaps, retention risk), and plan approval status. Supports headcount reporting, cost allocation, workforce planning cycles, CAPEX/OPEX labor budgeting, property-level staffing models, and leadership continuity planning. Sourced from ADP Workforce Now and SAP S/4HANA HCM.' .

ind:EmploymentEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Employment Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of all HR personnel actions and events affecting an employee\'s employment lifecycle, including disciplinary actions. Captures event type (hire, rehire, transfer, promotion, demotion, leave of absence, return from leave, termination, position change, compensation change, verbal warning, written warning, final written warning, suspension, termination for cause), effective date, reason code, prior and new values for changed attributes, policy violation details (for disciplinary events), investigation findings, approving manager, HR business partner, legal review indicator, appeal status, and event status. Sourced from ADP Workforce Now. Provides the complete employment history audit trail — both positive career progression and corrective actions — for each employee across their tenure. Supports wrongful termination defense, SOX internal controls, and HR compliance audits.' .

ind:Payroll rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Payroll' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Payroll processing records for all real estate employees, covering both run-level headers and individual employee-level results. Run data captures payroll run ID, pay period dates, pay date, frequency, payroll group, run status, total gross/net pay, employer tax liability, and GL posting reference. Employee result data captures gross earnings by component (base salary, overtime, commission, bonus, allowances), pre-tax deductions (401k, HSA, FSA, medical/dental/vision premiums), federal/state/local tax withholdings, post-tax deductions, net pay, payment method, and YTD accumulators. Sourced from ADP Workforce Now Payroll module. Supports payroll reconciliation, GL posting to Yardi/SAP, W-2 preparation, payroll audits, and compensation analytics.' .

ind:PayrollResult rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Payroll Result' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual employee-level payroll calculation results for each payroll run. Captures employee reference, payroll run reference, pay period dates, gross earnings by component (base salary, overtime, commission, bonus, allowances), pre-tax deductions (401k, HSA, FSA, medical/dental/vision premiums), federal/state/local tax withholdings, post-tax deductions, net pay, payment method (direct deposit, check), bank account reference, and YTD accumulators. Sourced from ADP Workforce Now. Supports W-2 preparation, payroll audits, and compensation analytics for real estate workforce.' .

ind:CompensationPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Compensation Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Compensation structures and pay plans assigned to employees across the real estate enterprise. Captures compensation plan type (salary, hourly, commission-based, draw-against-commission for brokers/leasing agents, hybrid), base pay rate, pay frequency, commission rate schedule reference, bonus target percentage, effective date, expiration date, approval status, and the job profile and grade band it applies to. Brokers and leasing agents may have commission-only or draw-against-commission plans. Property managers may have base plus performance bonus. Sourced from ADP Workforce Now Compensation module.' .

ind:Benefit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Benefit' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Catalog of employee benefit plans offered by the real estate enterprise and employee enrollment/election records for each plan year. Plan data captures plan name, type (medical, dental, vision, life, disability, 401k, HSA, FSA, commuter, EAP), carrier, plan year, coverage tiers, premium contributions, deductibles, 401k match formula, vesting schedule, and eligibility criteria. Enrollment data captures employee reference, enrollment event type (new hire, open enrollment, qualifying life event), coverage tier elected, contribution amounts, dependent coverage, effective dates, waiver indicator, and enrollment status. Sourced from ADP Workforce Now Benefits Administration module. Supports ACA compliance reporting (1095-C), benefits cost allocation, and COBRA administration for terminated employees.' .

ind:BenefitEnrollment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Benefit Enrollment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Employee elections and enrollments in benefit plans for each plan year. Captures employee reference, benefit plan reference, enrollment event type (new hire, open enrollment, qualifying life event), coverage tier elected, employee contribution amount, employer contribution amount, dependent coverage details, enrollment effective date, termination date, waiver indicator (employee declined coverage), and enrollment status. Sourced from ADP Workforce Now Benefits Administration. Supports ACA compliance reporting (1095-C), benefits cost allocation, and COBRA administration for terminated real estate employees.' .

ind:TimeEntry rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Time Entry' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual time and attendance records submitted by real estate employees for each work period. Captures employee reference, work date, clock-in time, clock-out time, total hours worked, overtime hours, pay code (regular, overtime, PTO, sick, holiday, jury duty, bereavement), project or property cost allocation code, approval status (submitted, approved, rejected), approving manager, and submission timestamp. Applicable to hourly field staff, maintenance technicians, construction workers, and any salaried employees tracking project time for CAPEX/OPEX allocation. Sourced from ADP Workforce Now Time and Attendance module.' .

ind:LeaveRequest rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Leave Request' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Employee leave of absence requests and approved leave records. Captures employee reference, leave type (FMLA, personal leave, military leave, parental leave, medical leave, sabbatical), requested start date, requested end date, approved start date, approved end date, leave reason, FMLA eligibility indicator, intermittent leave indicator, leave status (requested, approved, denied, in-progress, returned, cancelled), HR approver, return-to-work date, and accommodation notes. Sourced from ADP Workforce Now. Supports FMLA compliance tracking, workforce availability planning, and leave liability accrual for real estate operations.' .

ind:LicenseCertification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'License Certification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Professional licenses and certifications held by real estate workforce members, including renewal lifecycle tracking. Credential data captures employee reference, credential type (real estate broker license, salesperson license, appraiser license — Certified Residential, Certified General, Licensed Residential, MAI, LEED AP, BREEAM assessor, CPM, CCIM, RPA, FMA, PMP, OSHA 30, contractor license), issuing authority, license number, issue date, expiration date, jurisdiction (state/country), and CE hours required vs completed. Renewal data captures renewal cycle dates, renewal deadline, CE hours progress, application submission date, renewal fee, renewed license number, new expiration date, renewal status (pending, submitted, approved, lapsed, suspended), and regulatory body confirmation. Supports proactive license expiry alerts, multi-state compliance audits, and ensures brokers, appraisers, and property managers maintain active credentials required by state commissions, NAR, and the Appraisal Institute.' .

ind:LicenseRenewal rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'License Renewal' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional records tracking the renewal lifecycle of professional licenses and certifications for real estate workforce members. Captures license/certification reference, renewal cycle start date, renewal deadline, CE hours required for renewal, CE hours completed to date, renewal application submission date, renewal fee paid amount, renewed license number, new expiration date, renewal status (pending, submitted, approved, lapsed, suspended), and regulatory body confirmation reference. Supports proactive license expiry alerts, compliance audits, and ensures brokers, appraisers, and property managers maintain active credentials required by NAR, state commissions, and the Appraisal Institute.' .

ind:WorkforceTraining rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Workforce Training' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Catalog of training and professional development courses available to real estate workforce members, along with employee enrollment and completion records. Course data captures course code, title, category (compliance/mandatory, CE for license renewal, leadership development, technical skills, safety/OSHA, DEI, onboarding), delivery format, duration hours, CE credit hours, accrediting body, provider, cost per seat, and active status. Enrollment data captures employee reference, enrollment date, completion date, completion status (enrolled, in-progress, completed, failed, withdrawn, no-show), assessment score, CE hours earned, and certificate reference. Includes mandatory compliance training (Fair Housing Act, OSHA, SOX, anti-harassment) and elective professional development. Sourced from ADP Workforce Now Talent Management / LMS module. Supports compliance training completion rate reporting and CE hour tracking toward license renewals for brokers, appraisers, and property managers.' .

ind:TrainingEnrollment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Training Enrollment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Employee enrollments and completion records for training courses. Captures employee reference, training course reference, enrollment date, scheduled session date, completion date, completion status (enrolled, in-progress, completed, failed, withdrawn, no-show), assessment score, CE hours earned, certificate of completion reference, and cost charged to department. Tracks mandatory compliance training completion rates (Fair Housing, OSHA, anti-harassment, SOX) and CE hours earned toward license renewals for brokers, appraisers, and property managers. Sourced from ADP Workforce Now Talent Management module.' .

ind:PerformanceReview rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Performance Review' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Formal employee performance evaluation records conducted on a scheduled or ad-hoc basis. Captures employee reference, review period (annual, mid-year, probationary, project-based), review type, overall performance rating (e.g., exceeds expectations, meets expectations, needs improvement), individual goal ratings, competency ratings, manager comments, employee self-assessment reference, calibration status, merit increase recommendation, promotion recommendation, PIP (Performance Improvement Plan) indicator, review completion date, and approving HR business partner. Sourced from ADP Workforce Now Talent Management. Drives compensation decisions, succession planning, and talent development for real estate workforce.' .

ind:HeadcountPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Headcount Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Workforce planning and headcount budgeting records by department, property, or business unit for a planning period. Captures planning period (fiscal year, quarter), org unit reference, job profile reference, budgeted headcount (FTE), actual filled headcount, open requisition count, planned new hires, planned attrition, net headcount change, budgeted labor cost (salary + benefits), actual labor cost, variance, and plan approval status. Now also captures succession planning data for critical roles: successor candidates, readiness levels, development gaps, and retention risk. Supports annual workforce planning cycles, CAPEX/OPEX labor budgeting for development projects, property-level staffing models, and leadership continuity planning. Integrates with SAP S/4HANA for financial consolidation.' .

ind:Recruiting rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Recruiting' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Job requisitions and candidate pipeline records for talent acquisition across the real estate enterprise. Requisition data captures requisition number, position reference, job profile reference, hiring manager, recruiter, requisition type (backfill, new headcount, temporary, contract), department, work location, target dates, budget, status, sourcing channels (MLS job boards, LinkedIn, internal referral, staffing agency), and applicant count. Candidate data captures applicant name, contact information, application date, source channel, resume reference, years of experience, real estate license status (critical for brokerage/leasing roles), education level, application status (applied, screening, phone interview, in-person interview, offer extended, offer accepted, offer declined, rejected, withdrawn), and disposition reason. Sourced from ADP Workforce Now Talent Acquisition module. Supports EEOC applicant flow reporting and time-to-fill analytics.' .

ind:Applicant rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Applicant' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Candidate records for open job requisitions across the real estate enterprise. Captures applicant name, contact information, application date, job requisition reference, source channel (employee referral, job board, agency, direct application), resume reference, current employer, years of relevant experience, real estate license status (holds active broker/salesperson license — critical for brokerage and leasing roles), highest education level, application status (applied, screening, phone interview, in-person interview, offer extended, offer accepted, offer declined, rejected, withdrawn), and disposition reason. Sourced from ADP Workforce Now Talent Acquisition. Supports EEOC applicant flow reporting.' .

ind:WorkAssignment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Work Assignment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Operational assignments linking employees to specific properties, projects, development sites, or asset management portfolios for a defined period. Captures assignment type (property management, leasing territory, construction site, asset management portfolio, facility operations), assigned property or project reference, start and end dates, FTE allocation percentage, primary vs. secondary indicator, and assignment status. Enables property-level workforce tracking — which PM manages which building, which leasing agent covers which submarket, which construction superintendent is on which development project. Critical for cross-domain joins to property and development domains for operational reporting and cost allocation.' .

ind:CommissionRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Commission Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Employee-facing transactional records of commission earnings for brokers, leasing agents, and sales staff. Captures employee reference, deal reference (lease execution, property sale, acquisition), commission event type (lease commission, sale commission, referral fee, co-broker split, override commission), gross commission amount, split percentage, net commission to employee, draw balance offset for draw-against-commission plans, commission period, payment status (pending, approved, paid, clawed-back), and GL posting reference. Sourced from Salesforce CRM deal closure events and processed through ADP Workforce Now payroll. SSOT boundary: deal-level commission structures and split calculations are owned by the brokerage domain; this product owns the employee-facing earnings record for payroll processing, 1099 reporting for independent contractor brokers, and commission expense accrual.' .

ind:PropertySale rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Transaction ;
    rdfs:label 'Property Sale' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core master record for every property sale or disposition transaction — acquisition, disposition, REO sale, short sale, portfolio trade, or sale-leaseback — capturing executed purchase price, PSF pricing, earnest money terms, closing date, deal type classification, transaction status, and key deal economics (price, PSF, cap rate). Serves as the SSOT hub to which all transaction detail entities (PSA, closing statement, title, deed, financing, escrow, due diligence, parties, offers, documents) are linked via FK. Sourced from Yardi Voyager and CoStar comparable sales data.' .

ind:PurchaseAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Transaction ;
    rdfs:label 'Purchase Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records the executed purchase and sale agreement (PSA) for a property transaction, including offer price, contingency terms and deadlines (inspection, financing, appraisal, environmental, zoning, sale of existing home), earnest money terms, due diligence period, closing timeline, and agreement status (LOI, under contract, executed, terminated). Tracks all amendments, addenda, and contingency resolutions through the PSA lifecycle. Integrates with DocuSign CLM for digital execution.' .

ind:ClosingStatement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Transaction ;
    rdfs:label 'Closing Statement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captures the final settlement statement (HUD-1 / ALTA Settlement Statement) for a property transaction at closing, including gross sale price, prorations, credits, commissions, title insurance premiums, transfer taxes, loan payoffs, net proceeds to seller, and cash to close for buyer. Represents the authoritative financial record of the closing event. Sourced from title company and Yardi Voyager.' .

ind:ClosingStatementLine rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Transaction ;
    rdfs:label 'Closing Statement Line' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual line-item detail within a closing statement, capturing each charge, credit, proration, or adjustment — including description, debit/credit amount, party responsible (buyer or seller), and GL account mapping. Enables granular reconciliation of closing economics and supports Yardi Voyager GL integration.' .

ind:TitleSearch rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Transaction ;
    rdfs:label 'Title Search' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks the title search, title commitment, and title insurance policy for a property transaction. Captures ALTA title policy number, insurer, coverage amount, effective date, exceptions and exclusions, lien search results, encumbrances, easements, and COO status. Serves as the authoritative record of title transfer and chain of title. Integrates with ALTA standards.' .

ind:DeedTransfer rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Transaction ;
    rdfs:label 'Deed Transfer' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records the legal deed transfer event for a property, capturing deed type (warranty, quitclaim, special warranty, trustee), grantor, grantee, recording date, county recorder document number, legal description, consideration amount, transfer tax paid, and recording jurisdiction. Represents the official conveyance of real property ownership. Linked to ALTA title records.' .

ind:Financing rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Transaction ;
    rdfs:label 'Financing' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captures the financing structure for a property transaction, including loan type (ARM, FRM, CMBS, bridge, construction), lender name, loan amount, LTV ratio, interest rate, DSCR, loan-to-cost ratio, origination fees, PMI indicator, loan commitment date, and funding date. Tracks both acquisition financing and assumption of existing debt. Supports CMBS and RMBS reporting.' .

ind:Exchange1031 rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Transaction ;
    rdfs:label 'Exchange 1031' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages IRS Section 1031 like-kind exchange transactions for tax-deferred property dispositions. Captures relinquished property details, replacement property identification (up to 3-property rule or 200% rule), qualified intermediary (QI) name and account, exchange deadlines (45-day identification period, 180-day closing deadline), boot amount, deferred gain calculation, exchange type (simultaneous, delayed, reverse, Improvement/construction), and IRS compliance status. Tracks exchange fund balances held by QI. Critical for tax-deferred disposition strategies and IRS Form 8824 reporting.' .

ind:ReoDisposition rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Transaction ;
    rdfs:label 'Reo Disposition' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks Real Estate Owned (REO) asset disposition transactions, capturing foreclosure date, REO acquisition date, lender/servicer name, BPO value, list price, days on market, as-is condition rating, repair cost estimate, net recovery amount, and disposition method (MLS listing, auction, bulk sale). Supports lender REO portfolio management and loss mitigation reporting.' .

ind:DueDiligenceItem rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Transaction ;
    rdfs:label 'Due Diligence Item' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks individual due diligence tasks, inspections, and findings for a property transaction — environmental Phase I/II, structural/MEP inspection, zoning and entitlement review, ALTA survey, title search, financial audit, rent roll verification, estoppel review, and tenant interview. Captures responsible party, due date, completion date, finding summary, risk rating (red/yellow/green), remediation requirement, cost estimate, and go/no-go recommendation. Enables systematic tracking of all pre-closing diligence obligations and supports investment committee reporting and PSA contingency resolution.' .

ind:DealParty rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Transaction ;
    rdfs:label 'Deal Party' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Association entity capturing all parties and their roles in a property transaction — buyer, seller, buyer\'s broker, seller\'s broker, lender, title company, escrow agent, qualified intermediary (QI), attorney, appraiser, and guarantor. Records role type, entity classification (individual, corporation, REIT, trust, partnership, LLC), contact reference (FK to owner or external party), participation status, and commission split percentage where applicable. Enables multi-party deal tracking, commission allocation, and 1099-S reporting.' .

ind:Offer rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Transaction ;
    rdfs:label 'Offer' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records individual purchase offers submitted on a property, capturing offer price, offer date, financing contingency amount, inspection contingency period, closing date proposed, earnest money offered, escalation clause details, offer status (submitted, countered, accepted, rejected, withdrawn), and competing offer indicator. Supports multi-offer scenario management and deal pipeline tracking in Salesforce CRM.' .

ind:EscrowAccount rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Transaction ;
    rdfs:label 'Escrow Account' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages escrow accounts and the complete ledger of fund movements for property transactions — earnest money deposits, impound holds, disbursements (commissions, title fees, transfer taxes, loan payoffs, net proceeds), and releases. Captures escrow account number, escrow holder, escrow type (purchase, impound, reserve), opening balance, current balance, and account status. Each fund event records date, payee/payor, amount, payment method, reference number, authorization status, and release conditions. Provides a complete audit trail from account opening through final disbursement. Integrates with Yardi Voyager AP/AR for trust account reconciliation.' .

ind:EscrowDisbursement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Transaction ;
    rdfs:label 'Escrow Disbursement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records individual disbursement events from an escrow account, including disbursement date, payee, disbursement amount, disbursement type (commission, title fee, transfer tax, loan payoff, net proceeds), payment method, reference number, and authorization status. Provides a complete audit trail of all funds released from escrow at or after closing.' .

ind:TransactionDealDocument rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Transaction ;
    rdfs:label 'Transaction Deal Document' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Repository of all documents associated with a property transaction, including document type (PSA, amendment, disclosure, inspection report, appraisal, title commitment, deed, closing statement, SNDA, loan commitment), document name, version number, execution date, signatory parties, DocuSign envelope ID, storage path, and document status. Integrates with DocuSign CLM for executed document management.' .

ind:SaleType rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Transaction ;
    rdfs:label 'Sale Type' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference classification table defining standardized transaction type taxonomy — acquisition, disposition, 1031 exchange, REO sale, short sale, foreclosure, portfolio sale, sale-leaseback, and ground lease assignment. Captures type code, display name, transaction category (commercial, residential, land, mixed-use), applicable deal workflow template, and regulatory reporting flag. Used enterprise-wide to classify and filter property_sale records.' .

ind:TaxAllocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Investment ;
    rdfs:label 'Tax Allocation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records annual and quarterly tax allocations to investors in partnership-structured funds, including K-1 data, UBTI calculations, depreciation pass-throughs, Section 1031 exchange tracking, REIT dividend characterization (ordinary income, capital gain, return of capital), and state-level tax apportionment. Captures allocation period, investor reference, allocated taxable income/loss, depreciation allocated, capital gain allocated, UBTI amount, K-1 issuance date, and CPA review status. Required for IRS partnership reporting and investor tax compliance. Sourced from MRI Software and tax preparation systems.' .

ind:Guaranty rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Guaranty' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks lease guaranty and guarantor obligations for commercial lease agreements. Captures guarantor identity (individual, corporate parent, or entity), guaranty type (full, limited, good-guy, rolling), guaranteed amount or period, burn-down schedule, guarantor financial covenants, guaranty expiration triggers, and enforcement status. Critical for landlord credit risk management on commercial leases where tenant creditworthiness depends on a third-party guarantee. Sourced from DocuSign CLM and Yardi Voyager.' .

ind:Screening rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Tenant ;
    rdfs:label 'Screening' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tenant background screening and reference verification record capturing the results of employment verification, landlord reference checks, criminal background checks, identity verification (SSN/ITIN validation), and sex offender registry checks performed during the application qualification process. Records screening vendor (e.g., RentPrep, TransUnion SmartMove), screening request date, completion date, pass/fail determination per check type, adverse action notice requirement, and FCRA compliance status. Supports fair housing compliance, consistent screening criteria enforcement, and audit trail for adverse action decisions.' .

ind:Proforma rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Development ;
    rdfs:label 'Proforma' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Development pro forma and financial underwriting record for each real estate development project — the financial feasibility model that drives go/no-go investment decisions. Captures land acquisition cost, hard costs, soft costs, financing assumptions (construction loan terms, permanent loan takeout), projected revenue (sale proceeds or stabilized NOI), target IRR, target equity multiple, target yield on cost, development spread, sensitivity scenarios, waterfall distribution assumptions, and approval status. Updated through project lifecycle as actuals replace assumptions. Links to dev_project. SSOT for development financial underwriting within the development domain. Critical for investment committee approvals, lender underwriting packages, and investor reporting.' .

ind:Amenity rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Amenity' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Physical amenity record for a property or building — pools, fitness centers, parking structures, concierge services, rooftop decks, conference rooms, and other value-add features. Captures amenity type, location within property, capacity, operating hours, condition, and maintenance responsibility.' .

ind:CommonArea rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Common Area' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Common area record for shared spaces within a property or building — lobbies, hallways, elevators, stairwells, loading docks, and shared restrooms. Captures area type, square footage, maintenance responsibility, CAM allocation basis, and ADA compliance status.' .

ind:Parking rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Parking' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Parking facility and space inventory record for properties — surface lots, structured garages, underground parking, and reserved spaces. Captures total spaces, reserved vs unreserved counts, monthly rates, valet availability, EV charging stations, and ADA-compliant space counts.' .

ind:Campaign rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Campaign' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for every marketing campaign executed across commercial and residential portfolios. Captures campaign name, type (digital, print, OOH, email, social, event), objective (lead generation, brand awareness, listing promotion, market penetration), target audience segment, geographic market, property type focus, campaign status (draft, active, paused, completed), planned start and end dates, actual run dates, total approved budget, total spend to date, campaign owner, and associated brand or sub-brand. SSOT for campaign identity across all marketing activities.' .

ind:CampaignFlight rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Campaign Flight' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record representing a discrete execution flight or burst within a parent campaign — a specific channel activation, media buy, or ad run period. Captures flight name, channel type (Google Ads, Meta, CoStar, Zillow, LoopNet, email, direct mail, billboard), flight start and end dates, flight budget, impressions delivered, clicks, spend, placement details, creative asset reference, and flight status. Enables multi-channel campaign decomposition and channel-level performance tracking.' .

ind:AdCreative rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Ad Creative' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all marketing creative assets used in campaigns — property listing photos, virtual tour links, brochure PDFs, video walkthroughs, banner ads, email templates, social media graphics, and signage artwork. Captures creative name, format (image, video, PDF, HTML5, copy), dimensions or specs, file URL or DAM reference, associated property or portfolio, brand compliance status, approval status, version number, expiry date, and creative performance metadata. SSOT for creative asset inventory.' .

ind:ListingSyndication rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Listing Syndication' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record tracking the syndication of a property listing to external marketing portals and platforms — Zillow, Realtor.com, LoopNet, CoStar, Apartments.com, MLS, and proprietary websites. Captures listing reference, target platform, syndication status (pending, live, expired, pulled), publish date, expiry date, listing URL on platform, feed type (RETS, RESO Web API, IDX, manual), last sync timestamp, and any platform-specific override fields. Distinct from brokerage.mls_syndication which is brokerage-owned; this entity is marketing-owned for campaign-driven syndication.' .

ind:Lead rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Lead' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT master record for every inbound marketing lead generated across all channels — web inquiries, portal leads (Zillow, CoStar, LoopNet), email responses, open house sign-ins, social media DMs, referral submissions, and event registrations. Captures lead source, channel, campaign attribution, lead type (buyer, tenant, investor, seller), property of interest, contact details, lead status (new, contacted, qualified, disqualified, converted), lead score, assigned agent or leasing rep, first contact date, and last activity date. Distinct from brokerage.prospect (brokerage-owned pipeline) and tenant.prospect (tenancy-specific).' .

ind:LeadActivity rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Lead Activity' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing every discrete activity or touchpoint associated with a marketing lead — email opens, link clicks, portal page views, call attempts, SMS responses, chatbot interactions, and form submissions. Captures lead reference, activity type, activity timestamp, channel, campaign flight reference, content or page viewed, outcome, and agent or system that performed the action. Enables lead nurture tracking, attribution modeling, and conversion funnel analysis.' .

ind:LeadAttribution rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Lead Attribution' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Attribution record linking a converted lead to one or more marketing campaigns and channels using multi-touch attribution models (first-touch, last-touch, linear, time-decay, data-driven). Captures lead reference, conversion event type (lease signed, purchase agreement, showing booked), conversion date, attributed campaign references, attribution model used, attribution weight per campaign, attributed revenue or deal value, and attribution calculation timestamp. Enables ROI measurement per campaign and channel.' .

ind:DigitalListing rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Digital Listing' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Marketing-owned master record for the digital presentation of a property listing as published across owned and paid channels — the marketing-layer representation of a property for promotional purposes. Captures property reference, listing headline, marketing description copy, key selling points, asking price or rent range, property highlights, virtual tour URL, photo gallery references, floor plan URL, video URL, listing status (draft, active, under offer, leased, sold, archived), publish date, and SEO metadata. Distinct from brokerage.listing (brokerage transaction record) — this is the marketing content layer.' .

ind:MarketResearch rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Market Research' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for formal market research studies, competitive intelligence reports, and market analysis engagements commissioned or produced by the marketing team. Captures research title, research type (submarket analysis, competitive landscape, demand study, absorption study, rent survey, buyer sentiment), geographic market or submarket, property type focus, research date, research provider (internal or third-party firm), key findings summary, report file URL, data sources used, and publication status. SSOT for market intelligence assets.' .

ind:CompetitorProperty rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Competitor Property' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for competitor properties tracked as part of competitive market intelligence — comparable properties in the same submarket used for competitive positioning, pricing benchmarking, and marketing strategy. Captures competitor property name, address, owner or operator name, property type, building class, total rentable area, number of units, asking rent or price, occupancy rate, amenities, marketing channels used, last verified date, and data source (CoStar, LoopNet, field survey, broker intel). Enables competitive set monitoring.' .

ind:MarketSurvey rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Market Survey' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of a periodic market survey event capturing point-in-time competitive market data for a defined submarket or competitive set — rent surveys, vacancy surveys, absorption surveys, and concession surveys. Captures survey date, submarket or geographic area, property type, survey type, surveyor name, number of properties surveyed, average asking rent, average effective rent, vacancy rate, absorption rate, average concession value, and survey notes. Enables trend tracking and market positioning decisions.' .

ind:MarketingBudget rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Marketing Budget' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Marketing-domain budget record defining the approved marketing spend allocation by campaign, channel, property, portfolio, or fiscal period. Captures budget name, fiscal year, budget period (annual, quarterly, monthly), property or portfolio reference, campaign reference, channel type, approved budget amount, revised budget amount, committed spend, actual spend to date, variance, budget owner, approval date, and approval status. Distinct from finance.budget (enterprise GL budget) — this is the marketing operational spend plan.' .

ind:AdSpend rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Ad Spend' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of actual advertising expenditure events — individual media buys, platform charges, agency invoices, and production costs incurred against a campaign flight or marketing budget. Captures spend date, vendor or platform name, campaign flight reference, marketing budget reference, spend category (media placement, creative production, agency fee, event cost, print), invoice reference, amount, currency, payment status, and cost center. Enables granular spend tracking and budget reconciliation.' .

ind:Event rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for marketing events organized or sponsored by the real estate enterprise — open houses, broker previews, investor days, property launch events, community outreach events, trade show participations, and webinars. Captures event name, event type, property or portfolio reference, venue, event date and time, target audience, expected attendance, actual attendance, registration count, event status, event owner, associated campaign reference, and total event cost. Enables event-driven lead generation tracking.' .

ind:EventRegistration rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Event Registration' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of an individual registrant or attendee for a marketing event — capturing registration date, registrant contact details, registrant type (prospect, broker, investor, tenant, media), registration source, attendance status (registered, attended, no-show, cancelled), lead reference if converted, and post-event follow-up status. Enables event ROI measurement and lead capture from event-driven marketing activities.' .

ind:Brand rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Brand' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for brand identities managed within the real estate enterprise — corporate brand, sub-brands for specific property portfolios, residential community brands, commercial park brands, and co-branded partnerships. Captures brand name, brand tier (corporate, portfolio, property-level), brand guidelines URL, logo asset reference, color palette, typography standards, brand owner, brand launch date, brand status (active, retired, in development), and associated markets or property types. SSOT for brand identity governance.' .

ind:Channel rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Channel' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference master for all marketing channels used to reach prospects, tenants, buyers, and investors — defining the standardized channel taxonomy across the enterprise. Captures channel name, channel category (digital paid, digital organic, social media, email, direct mail, OOH, events, referral, broker network, MLS/portal), channel description, platform or vendor name, tracking capability (UTM, pixel, call tracking), cost model (CPM, CPC, CPL, flat fee), and channel status. Enables consistent channel attribution and spend categorization.' .

ind:AudienceSegment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Audience Segment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record defining target audience segments used for campaign targeting and personalization — buyer personas, investor profiles, tenant segments, and demographic cohorts relevant to real estate marketing. Captures segment name, segment type (demographic, behavioral, psychographic, firmographic for B2B), target property type, income or net worth band, geographic preference, life stage (first-time buyer, move-up buyer, empty nester, institutional investor), segment size estimate, data source, and segment owner. Enables precision targeting across campaigns.' .

ind:EmailCampaign rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Email Campaign' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for email marketing campaign executions — property newsletters, listing alerts, market update emails, drip nurture sequences, and investor communications. Captures email campaign name, parent campaign reference, email template reference, subject line, sender name and address, target audience segment, send date and time, total recipients, delivered count, open count, click count, unsubscribe count, bounce count, and email service provider reference (Mailchimp, HubSpot, Salesforce Marketing Cloud). Enables email channel performance tracking.' .

ind:SeoKeyword rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Seo Keyword' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for SEO and SEM keywords tracked and managed as part of the digital marketing strategy for property listings and brand visibility. Captures keyword phrase, keyword type (branded, non-branded, long-tail, local), target property type, target geographic market, search volume, competition level, current ranking position, target ranking position, associated landing page URL, bid amount for paid search, quality score, and last updated date. Enables organic and paid search optimization for property marketing.' .

ind:SocialPost rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Social Post' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for individual social media posts published as part of marketing campaigns or organic brand presence — property listings, market updates, community highlights, and investor content across LinkedIn, Instagram, Facebook, X (Twitter), and YouTube. Captures platform, post type (organic, paid, boosted), post content text, media asset references, publish date and time, campaign flight reference, target audience, reach, impressions, engagements (likes, comments, shares), link clicks, and post status. Enables social channel performance tracking.' .

ind:ContentCalendar rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Content Calendar' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for the marketing content calendar — the planned schedule of content publications, campaign launches, listing promotions, and marketing activities across all channels for a defined period. Captures calendar name, planning period (month, quarter), property or portfolio scope, planned content items count, channel mix, key dates (property launches, lease-up milestones, market events), calendar owner, approval status, and last updated date. Enables coordinated multi-channel marketing execution planning.' .

ind:Vendor rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for external marketing vendors, agencies, and service providers engaged by the marketing team — advertising agencies, digital marketing firms, photography studios, virtual tour providers, print vendors, media buying agencies, PR firms, and market research companies. Captures vendor name, vendor type, services provided, contract reference, primary contact, engagement start and end dates, rate card or fee structure, preferred vendor status, performance rating, and vendor status. Distinct from general procurement — this is the marketing-domain vendor registry.' .

ind:PressRelease rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Press Release' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for press releases and public relations communications issued by the real estate enterprise — property acquisition announcements, development groundbreakings, lease signings, award recognitions, executive appointments, and market commentary. Captures headline, release date, embargo date, distribution wire service (PR Newswire, BusinessWire), target media outlets, property or transaction reference, author, approval status, published URL, and media pickup count. Supports brand management and investor relations communications.' .

ind:CampaignProperty rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Campaign Property' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Association entity linking a marketing campaign to the specific properties or portfolio assets being promoted within that campaign. Captures campaign reference, property asset reference, property role in campaign (featured property, portfolio showcase, comparable reference), inclusion start and end dates, property-specific budget allocation, property-specific lead count, and listing URL used in campaign. Enables property-level campaign attribution and multi-property campaign management.' .

ind:Policy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Policy' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for every property and liability insurance policy held across the real estate portfolio. Captures policy number, insurer name, policy type (property, general liability, umbrella, D&O, workers comp, flood, earthquake, terrorism, title), coverage class, policy status (active, expired, cancelled, non-renewed), effective date, expiration date, renewal date, premium amount, payment frequency, insured value, total insurable value (TIV), deductible structure, coverage limits, sub-limits, coinsurance percentage, policy form, endorsements summary, broker of record, and the legal entity or property asset the policy covers. SSOT for all insurance policy master data across the portfolio.' .

ind:Coverage rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Coverage' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Granular coverage line record defining each distinct coverage layer or peril within an insurance policy. Captures coverage type (building, business interruption, general liability, umbrella, flood, earthquake, terrorism, boiler and machinery), coverage limit, sub-limit, deductible amount, deductible type (per-occurrence, aggregate, percentage of TIV), coinsurance clause, agreed value endorsement flag, replacement cost vs. actual cash value basis, coverage territory, and effective/expiration dates. One policy may have multiple coverage lines. Enables per-peril limit analysis and gap identification.' .

ind:InsuredProperty rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Insured Property' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Association entity linking an insurance policy to the specific real estate assets (properties, buildings, parcels) covered under that policy. Captures insured property reference, scheduled property address, insured value at policy inception, replacement cost value (RCV), actual cash value (ACV), building square footage, year built, construction type, occupancy type, protection class, COPE (Construction, Occupancy, Protection, Exposure) data, flood zone designation, seismic zone, and whether the property is a scheduled location or blanket-covered. Supports TIV roll-up and per-location coverage analysis.' .

ind:StatementOfValues rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Statement Of Values' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Periodic Statement of Values (SOV) record submitted to insurers at policy inception and renewal, listing all scheduled properties and their insured values. Captures SOV version, submission date, total insurable value (TIV), number of locations, valuation basis (replacement cost, ACV, agreed value), appraisal reference, and submission status. Tracks SOV revisions mid-term when properties are acquired or disposed. Critical for ensuring adequate coverage and avoiding coinsurance penalties at claim time.' .

ind:Premium rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Premium' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Insurance premium billing and payment record tracking all premium charges, installments, and payments for each policy. Captures premium type (base premium, endorsement premium, audit premium, minimum earned premium), billing period, due date, amount billed, amount paid, payment date, payment method, carrier invoice reference, surplus lines tax, stamping fee, broker commission, net premium, and payment status (current, past due, lapsed). Supports premium allocation across properties and cost centers for financial reporting.' .

ind:Claim rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Claim' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core transactional record for every insurance claim filed against a policy in the real estate portfolio. Captures claim number, date of loss, date reported, cause of loss (fire, water damage, wind, theft, liability, flood, earthquake), loss description, claim type (property damage, business interruption, liability, workers comp), claim status (open, closed, denied, subrogation, litigation), claimant identity, adjuster assigned, reserve amount, total incurred loss, total paid loss, deductible applied, net claim payment, and subrogation recovery. SSOT for all loss events across the portfolio.' .

ind:ClaimPayment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Claim Payment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual payment disbursement record within an insurance claim lifecycle. Captures payment number, payment date, payee name, payee type (insured, mortgagee, contractor, claimant), payment amount, payment type (advance, partial, final, supplemental, subrogation recovery), check or wire reference, coverage line applied, reserve reduction amount, and cumulative paid-to-date. Enables granular tracking of multi-payment claims and mortgagee co-payment requirements.' .

ind:LossRun rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Loss Run' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Loss run report record capturing the historical claims experience for a policy or portfolio over a defined period, as provided by the insurer. Captures loss run period (typically 5 years), insurer name, policy number, number of claims, total incurred losses, total paid losses, total open reserves, largest single loss, loss ratio, and loss run request date. Used for renewal underwriting submissions, broker negotiations, and actuarial reserve analysis. Tracks each loss run version received from carriers.' .

ind:RiskAssessment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Risk Assessment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Property-level risk assessment record capturing the underwriting risk profile and hazard evaluation for insured real estate assets. Captures assessment date, assessor type (internal risk manager, third-party engineer, insurer inspector), risk score, hazard categories identified (fire, flood, wind, seismic, environmental, crime), COPE data summary, protection class rating, fire suppression system status, roof condition, electrical system age, plumbing condition, prior loss history flag, recommended risk improvements, and assessment outcome (acceptable, conditional, declined). Drives underwriting decisions and premium pricing.' .

ind:CertificateOfInsurance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Certificate Of Insurance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Certificate of Insurance (COI) record issued to or received from third parties as evidence of insurance coverage. Captures certificate number, certificate type (issued to tenant, lender, contractor, municipality; or received from vendor/contractor), certificate holder name and address, policy references, coverage types evidenced, coverage limits, effective and expiration dates, additional insured status, waiver of subrogation flag, primary and non-contributory endorsement flag, and certificate status (current, expiring, expired). Critical for lease compliance, lender requirements, and vendor management.' .

ind:Renewal rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Renewal' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Policy renewal lifecycle management record tracking the end-to-end renewal process for each expiring insurance policy. Captures renewal cycle year, renewal initiation date, expiration date, renewal status (in progress, submitted to market, quoted, bound, lapsed), incumbent carrier retention flag, marketing strategy (single carrier, competitive bid), renewal premium quoted, renewal premium bound, premium change vs. prior year (dollar and percentage), coverage changes at renewal, broker submission date, carrier quote deadline, binding date, and renewal notes. Enables proactive renewal management across the portfolio.' .

ind:Endorsement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Endorsement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Policy endorsement record capturing mid-term changes, additions, or modifications to an in-force insurance policy. Captures endorsement number, endorsement type (additional insured, location add/delete, coverage change, limit change, exclusion addition, waiver of subrogation), effective date, premium adjustment (additional or return premium), endorsement reason, requesting party, carrier approval date, and endorsement status. Tracks the full amendment history of each policy between inception and expiration.' .

ind:Insurer rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Insurer' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master registry of insurance carriers, syndicates, and reinsurers providing coverage to the real estate portfolio. Captures insurer legal name, NAIC company code, AM Best rating, AM Best financial size category, surplus lines eligibility flag, state admittance status, insurer type (admitted, non-admitted, Lloyd\'s syndicate, captive), primary contact, claims contact, underwriting contact, and insurer status (active, inactive, in run-off). Supports carrier financial strength monitoring and regulatory compliance for surplus lines placements.' .

ind:InsuranceBroker rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Insurance Broker' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for insurance brokers, agents, and risk management consultants engaged to place and service insurance programs for the real estate portfolio. Captures broker firm name, broker license number, state licenses held, broker type (retail, wholesale, surplus lines, captive manager), primary contact, account executive assigned, broker of record status, errors and omissions (E&O) coverage limit, E&O expiration date, brokerage commission rate, and broker status. Distinct from brokerage.broker (real estate sales/leasing brokers) — this entity represents insurance intermediaries.' .

ind:Adjuster rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Adjuster' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for insurance adjusters and independent adjusting firms assigned to evaluate and settle claims against the real estate portfolio. Captures adjuster name, adjuster type (staff adjuster, independent adjuster, public adjuster, catastrophe adjuster), firm name, license number, states licensed, contact information, adjuster specialty (property, liability, business interruption, large loss), current claim assignment count, and adjuster status. Enables claim assignment tracking and adjuster performance monitoring.' .

ind:ClaimReserve rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Claim Reserve' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reserve establishment and adjustment record tracking the financial reserves set by the insurer or TPA for each open claim. Captures reserve type (indemnity reserve, expense reserve, IBNR), reserve amount established, reserve change amount, reserve change reason, reserve change date, adjuster authorization, cumulative reserve, and reserve adequacy flag. Tracks the full reserve history for each claim from opening through closure. Critical for loss forecasting, financial reporting, and actuarial analysis.' .

ind:LiabilityEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Liability Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Liability incident and third-party claim event record capturing occurrences at managed properties that may give rise to general liability, premises liability, or professional liability claims. Captures incident date, incident location (property, building, common area), incident type (slip and fall, property damage to third party, bodily injury, wrongful eviction, discrimination allegation), injured party description, witness information, incident description, police report reference, medical treatment sought flag, notice of claim received flag, and litigation status. Feeds into the claim record when a formal claim is filed.' .

ind:CaptiveAccount rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Captive Account' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captive insurance program account record for real estate enterprises that self-insure through a captive insurance vehicle. Captures captive entity name, domicile jurisdiction, captive type (single-parent, group, rent-a-captive, cell captive), lines of business written, capitalization amount, retained limit per occurrence, aggregate retention, fronting carrier arrangement, reinsurance structure, captive premium ceded, loss fund balance, and regulatory filing status. Supports captive program management and financial reporting for self-insurance structures.' .

ind:InsuranceProgram rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Insurance Program' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Insurance program master record defining the enterprise-level insurance program structure for a given policy year. Captures program name, program year, program type (property, casualty, management liability, environmental, construction wrap-up, OCIP/CCIP), total program premium, total TIV covered, number of policies in program, primary carrier, excess/umbrella tower structure, program inception and expiration dates, broker of record, risk management contact, and program status. Provides the top-level view of the insurance portfolio structure for a given year.' .

ind:ExcessLayer rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Excess Layer' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Excess and umbrella insurance layer record defining each layer in the coverage tower above the primary policy. Captures layer number, layer type (first excess, second excess, umbrella, quota share), attaching limit (attachment point), layer limit, total layer capacity, participating insurer(s), each insurer\'s share percentage, layer premium, and layer status. Models the full excess tower structure for property catastrophe, general liability, and D&O programs. Essential for large real estate portfolios with complex layered programs.' .

ind:PremiumAllocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Premium Allocation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Premium cost allocation record distributing insurance premium charges across properties, cost centers, legal entities, and business units for internal financial reporting and budgeting. Captures allocation method (pro-rata by TIV, square footage, revenue, equal split), allocated premium amount, allocation period, property reference, cost center reference, legal entity reference, and allocation status. Enables property-level insurance cost tracking and NOI impact analysis.' .

ind:Subrogation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Subrogation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Subrogation recovery record tracking the insurer\'s right to pursue third parties responsible for insured losses. Captures subrogation claim reference, responsible party identity, subrogation basis (negligence, product liability, contractor fault), demand amount, recovery amount received, recovery date, legal counsel engaged, litigation status, statute of limitations date, and subrogation outcome (recovered, settled, waived, uncollectible). Reduces net loss costs and supports recovery accounting.' .

ind:PolicyDocument rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Policy Document' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Document repository record for all insurance-related documents associated with policies, claims, renewals, and risk assessments. Captures document type (policy form, endorsement, binder, certificate, loss run, appraisal, risk engineering report, claim correspondence, proof of loss, reservation of rights letter), document title, document date, file reference, storage location, version number, and document status. Provides a complete document audit trail for each insurance policy and claim lifecycle.' .

ind:EnergyMeter rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Maintenance ;
    rdfs:label 'Energy Meter' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for utility meters and energy monitoring devices installed at managed properties — electric, gas, water, and steam meters. Captures meter ID, meter type, utility provider account number, installation location (building, floor, unit), read frequency, and current status. Supports utility cost allocation, energy benchmarking, and sustainability reporting.' .

ind:MeterAllocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Meter Allocation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the allocation relationship between lease agreements and energy meters in sub-metered commercial properties. It captures utility cost allocation, billing responsibility, and CAM reconciliation data. Each record links one lease agreement to one energy meter with allocation percentages, billing periods, and utility type classifications that exist only in the context of this relationship. Supports tenant utility billing, CAM reconciliation, and ESG reporting workflows.. Existence Justification: In sub-metered commercial real estate, one lease agreement can be responsible for multiple utility meters (e.g., electric, gas, water, HVAC serving the leased suite), and one meter can serve multiple lease agreements in shared spaces (e.g., common area HVAC, shared water meters in multi-tenant buildings). Property managers actively manage meter allocations as a distinct business process, configuring allocation percentages, billing periods, and CAM billable flags when leases are executed and updating them during lease modifications or meter reconfigurations.' .

ind:Assignment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Assignment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the operational assignment of workforce personnel to real estate assets. It captures the formal relationship between employees and the properties they manage, lease, maintain, or operate. Each record links one employee to one asset with role-specific attributes including assignment dates, FTE allocation, managed square footage, and primary assignment designation. This is the authoritative source for answering \'who is responsible for which property\' and \'what properties does this employee manage\'.. Existence Justification: In real estate operations, employees are routinely assigned to multiple assets simultaneously (e.g., a regional property manager oversees 8 office buildings, a leasing agent covers 3 retail centers), and assets require multiple specialized staff (e.g., a Class A tower has a property manager, assistant property manager, chief engineer, leasing director, and facilities coordinator). The detection reasoning explicitly confirms that a work_assignment product already exists modeling this junction with role, FTE allocation, start/end dates, and managed GLA—proving this is an actively managed operational relationship, not an analytical correlation.' .

ind:BuildingPolicyCoverage rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Building Policy Coverage' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Schedule of Locations (SOV) entry linking each building to each insurance policy that covers it. In commercial real estate insurance, a single blanket policy typically covers multiple buildings across a portfolio, and a single building may be covered under multiple policies simultaneously (e.g., property policy + flood policy + earthquake policy). Each record captures the building-specific coverage terms, insured value, deductible, and coinsurance percentage as documented in the insurers Schedule of Locations. This is the SSOT for building-level insurance coverage terms and is used for certificate of insurance generation, claims processing, and insurance compliance reporting.. Existence Justification: In commercial real estate insurance, a single blanket policy routinely covers multiple buildings across a portfolio (one policy → many buildings), and a single building is simultaneously covered under multiple policies for different perils (one building → many policies: property, flood, earthquake, terrorism). Insurers document this via a Schedule of Locations (SOV), an industry-standard artifact that lists each building with its location number, insured value, deductible, coinsurance percentage, and coverage dates. This is an operational business entity actively managed by risk managers and insurers.' .

ind:PropertyOccupancy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Property Occupancy' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the commercial lease occupancy relationship between a space and a tenant. It captures the operational leasing arrangement including leased area, rent terms, CAM allocation, and occupancy period. Each record links one space to one tenant with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific lease arrangement.. Existence Justification: In commercial real estate operations, a single space can be simultaneously leased to multiple tenants through co-tenancy arrangements (e.g., shared conference rooms, co-working spaces, multi-tenant floors with subdivided areas), and a single tenant frequently leases multiple spaces across a building or portfolio (e.g., corporate headquarters spanning multiple floors, retail chains with multiple units). Each space-tenant combination represents a distinct lease arrangement with its own leased area, rent rate, CAM allocation, and term dates that cannot be stored on either the space or tenant entity alone.' .

ind:PropertyDemisedSpace rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Property Demised Space' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the contractual allocation of physical space to a lease agreement. It captures the specific spaces covered under each lease, including effective dates, rent rates, and area measurements that exist only in the context of this space-lease relationship. Each record links one space to one agreement with attributes that reflect the terms and conditions specific to that space within the broader lease.. Existence Justification: In real estate lease administration, a single physical space can be leased under multiple agreements over time (successive leases) and occasionally split across concurrent agreements for partial occupancy or subleasing scenarios. Conversely, a single lease agreement frequently covers multiple spaces (multi-space leases, entire floors, or suites comprising multiple rooms). The business actively manages the space-lease relationship with specific effective dates, rent rates per space, area measurements as stated in each lease, and status tracking for each space within each agreement.' .

ind:CampaignUnitInclusion rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Campaign Unit Inclusion' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the inclusion of a specific unit in a marketing campaign. It captures the operational relationship between property inventory and marketing activities. Each record links one unit to one campaign with attributes that track when the unit was featured, at what asking rent, with what priority level, and what budget was allocated to promote that specific unit within the campaign.. Existence Justification: In real estate marketing operations, a single unit can be simultaneously featured across multiple campaigns (e.g., a vacant unit appears in a lease-up campaign, a seasonal promotion, and a referral incentive campaign at the same time), and a single campaign typically promotes multiple units (e.g., a building lease-up campaign features 20+ available units). Marketing teams actively manage these inclusions, adjusting which units are featured, at what priority, and with what budget allocation as vacancy and market conditions change.' .

ind:RegulatoryApplicability rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Regulatory Applicability' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the applicability relationship between lease agreements and regulatory obligations. It captures which regulatory obligations apply to which lease agreements, when the obligation became applicable, current compliance status, any exemptions granted, and monitoring requirements. Each record links one lease agreement to one regulatory obligation with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific applicability relationship.. Existence Justification: In real estate operations, a single lease agreement is simultaneously subject to multiple regulatory obligations (rent control, fair housing, ADA accessibility, environmental compliance, zoning, fire safety, etc.). Each regulatory obligation applies to many lease agreements across the portfolio. Compliance teams actively manage these applicability relationships, tracking when each obligation became applicable to each lease, monitoring compliance status, documenting exemptions, and scheduling compliance checks at lease-specific frequencies.' .

ind:Enrollment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Enrollment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the enrollment relationship between lease agreements and compliance programs. It captures the operational reality that a single lease agreement can be enrolled in multiple compliance programs simultaneously (e.g., affordable housing, rent stabilization, LIHTC, green lease certification), and each compliance program covers many lease agreements across the portfolio. Each record links one lease agreement to one compliance program with enrollment-specific attributes that exist only in the context of this relationship, including enrollment dates, compliance status, program-specific scores, review schedules, and exemption flags tracked by compliance teams for regulatory reporting and program management.. Existence Justification: In real estate compliance operations, lease agreements are routinely enrolled in multiple compliance programs simultaneously—a single affordable housing lease may be enrolled in HUD Fair Housing, local rent stabilization, LIHTC tax credit, and green lease certification programs at the same time. Each compliance program covers hundreds or thousands of lease agreements across the portfolio. Compliance teams actively manage these enrollments as operational records, tracking enrollment dates, program-specific compliance scores, review schedules, exemptions, and status changes for regulatory reporting and audit purposes.' .

ind:BrokerProgramEnrollment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Broker Program Enrollment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the enrollment relationship between licensed brokers and enterprise compliance programs. It captures the operational reality that brokers must participate in multiple mandatory compliance programs (Fair Housing, AML, Continuing Education, E&O Insurance) and each program covers many brokers across the brokerage. Each record links one broker to one compliance program with enrollment-specific attributes including enrollment date, completion status, compliance score, renewal tracking, and assigned role within the program. This is an actively managed operational entity — compliance officers create enrollments, track completion, monitor scores, and manage renewals as part of regulatory obligation management.. Existence Justification: In real estate brokerage operations, licensed brokers must participate in multiple mandatory compliance programs simultaneously (Fair Housing training, Anti-Money Laundering certification, Continuing Education requirements, Errors & Omissions insurance compliance, state-specific regulatory programs). Each compliance program covers many brokers across the brokerage organization. Compliance officers actively manage these enrollments as operational records — they enroll brokers in programs, track completion status, monitor compliance scores, manage renewal deadlines, and assign program-specific roles. This is not an analytical correlation derived from transactional data; it is an operational business entity that humans create, update, and query as part of regulatory obligation management.' .

ind:BuildingComplianceObligation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Building Compliance Obligation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the applicability and compliance tracking of regulatory obligations to specific buildings. It captures which obligations apply to which buildings, the current compliance status, responsible parties, and key compliance dates. Each record links one building to one regulatory obligation with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific building-obligation pairing.. Existence Justification: In real estate operations, each building is subject to multiple regulatory obligations (fire codes, ADA compliance, energy benchmarking, elevator inspections, environmental permits, zoning requirements), and each regulatory obligation applies to multiple buildings across the portfolio. The compliance team actively manages this relationship by tracking applicability status, compliance status, responsible parties, certification numbers, review dates, and remediation activities for each building-obligation pairing. This is an operational compliance management process, not an analytical correlation.' .

ind:BuildingCertification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Building Certification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the certification relationship between a building and a sustainability rating scheme. It captures the specific certification achievement for a building under a particular rating system. Each record links one building to one sustainability rating level with attributes that exist only in the context of this certification event: the score achieved, dates of certification and expiry, certifying body reference, and current status. This is the operational record of green building certifications managed by ESG and sustainability teams.. Existence Justification: In real estate ESG operations, buildings routinely hold multiple sustainability certifications simultaneously (e.g., LEED Gold + ENERGY STAR + BREEAM Excellent + WELL Silver) to meet diverse investor, tenant, and regulatory requirements. Each certification scheme can be held by thousands of buildings across a portfolio. The business actively manages these certifications as operational records with specific scores, award dates, expiry dates, renewal cycles, and statuses that belong to the building-scheme combination, not to either entity alone.' .

ind:AssetServiceCoverage rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Maintenance ;
    rdfs:label 'Asset Service Coverage' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the contractual coverage relationship between building assets and maintenance service contracts. It captures which specific assets are covered under which service agreements, with coverage-specific terms that exist only in the context of this relationship. Each record links one building asset to one service contract with attributes defining the scope, duration, and service level commitments for that specific asset under that specific contract.. Existence Justification: In real estate facility management, building assets routinely have overlapping service coverage from multiple contracts (manufacturer warranty service, independent maintenance agreements, specialized system contracts), and service contracts routinely cover dozens to hundreds of individual assets across properties. The service_contract.covered_equipment_description STRING field is a denormalized representation that cannot support asset-specific coverage terms, SLAs, or coverage history tracking.' .

ind:AssetCoverageSchedule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Maintenance ;
    rdfs:label 'Asset Coverage Schedule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the scheduled insurance coverage relationship between building assets and insurance coverage lines. In real estate insurance, major building equipment (boilers, chillers, elevators, HVAC systems) are individually scheduled on equipment breakdown, boiler and machinery, or inland marine coverage lines. Each record captures the insured value, deductible, coverage limits, and effective dates specific to that asset-coverage pairing. A single building asset may appear on multiple coverage lines across different policy years or coverage types, and a single coverage line may schedule multiple high-value assets. This is the operational record used by risk managers to verify adequate coverage per asset and by claims adjusters to determine coverage applicability.. Existence Justification: In real estate insurance operations, high-value building equipment (boilers, chillers, elevators, HVAC systems, generators) are individually scheduled on equipment breakdown, boiler and machinery, or inland marine coverage lines. A single building asset can appear on multiple coverage lines across different policy years, coverage types, or insurers, and a single coverage line typically schedules multiple assets. Risk managers actively manage these schedules, assigning insured values, deductibles, and effective dates specific to each asset-coverage pairing.' .

ind:CamChargeAllocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Cam Charge Allocation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the allocation relationship between annual CAM reconciliations and individual billable maintenance charges. It captures how specific maintenance charges are included in tenant CAM reconciliation calculations, including the allocation method applied, the pro-rata share used for this specific charge-to-reconciliation pairing, the reconciliation year context, charge inclusion status, and any dispute flags. Each record links one CAM reconciliation to one billable charge with allocation-specific attributes that exist only in the context of this relationship. Critical for CAM audit trails and tenant dispute resolution.. Existence Justification: In real estate CAM reconciliation operations, one annual CAM reconciliation aggregates many individual billable maintenance charges (HVAC repairs, janitorial services, landscaping, etc.) into the tenant\'s annual expense calculation. Simultaneously, a single billable maintenance charge can be allocated across multiple tenant CAM reconciliations when the charge is part of a shared CAM pool serving multiple tenants in the same building. Property accountants actively manage these allocations, tracking which charges are included in which reconciliations, with what allocation method, pro-rata share, and inclusion status.' .

ind:CostAllocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Cost Allocation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the allocation of employee compensation and benefits across multiple cost centers in the real estate portfolio. It captures the financial distribution of workforce costs when employees work across multiple properties, departments, or business units. Each record links one employee to one cost center with allocation percentage, effective dates, and primary assignment flag. This is essential for accurate NOI reporting, OPEX tracking, and multi-property financial consolidation in real estate operations.. Existence Justification: In real estate operations, employees (especially property managers, asset managers, and regional staff) are routinely allocated across multiple cost centers representing different properties or business units, with each cost center having multiple employees. The business actively manages these allocations with specific percentages, effective dates, and primary assignment flags for accurate NOI reporting and OPEX tracking. This is standard split-cost accounting in multi-property real estate firms.' .

ind:DealCompliance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Deal Compliance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the compliance obligation tracking between brokerage deals and regulatory requirements. It captures the per-deal compliance status, evidence submission, responsible party assignment, and waiver management for each requirement that must be satisfied before deal close. Each record links one deal to one compliance requirement with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific deal-requirement relationship.. Existence Justification: In commercial real estate brokerage operations, each deal must satisfy multiple compliance requirements (environmental disclosure, ADA certification, zoning confirmation, FIRPTA, transfer tax documentation) before closing, and each compliance requirement applies to many deals across the portfolio. The business actively manages per-deal compliance tracking as a critical deal-closing workflow, with brokers and transaction coordinators monitoring status, assigning responsible parties, collecting evidence, and managing waivers for each deal-requirement combination.' .

ind:ProjectAssignment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Development ;
    rdfs:label 'Project Assignment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Assignment between dev_project and employee. It captures the staffing and role allocation of workforce personnel to real estate development projects. Each record links one development project to one employee with attributes that define their role, allocation percentage, tenure, and primary contact status on that specific project. Supports project staffing reports, CAPEX labor allocation tracking, and multi-project resource management.. Existence Justification: In real estate development operations, a single project requires a cross-functional team with multiple employees serving in distinct roles (Project Manager, Development Analyst, Legal Counsel, Finance Lead, Construction Manager), and individual employees—especially senior staff—work across multiple concurrent projects with varying allocation percentages. The business actively manages these assignments, tracking role, allocation percentage, tenure, and primary contact designation for each employee-project pairing. This is an operational staffing process, not an analytical correlation.' .

ind:ProjectBrokerEngagement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Development ;
    rdfs:label 'Project Broker Engagement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the engagement contract between a development project and a licensed broker. It captures the specific role, transaction type, commission arrangement, and engagement period for each broker working on a development project. Each record links one development project to one broker with attributes that exist only in the context of this professional engagement relationship.. Existence Justification: In real estate development, a single development project engages multiple brokers across different phases and transaction types (e.g., one broker for land acquisition, another for lease-up, a third for disposition). Conversely, a successful broker works on multiple development projects simultaneously or over their career. Each engagement is a distinct business contract with its own role, commission terms, engagement period, and performance targets.' .

ind:CampaignContribution rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Marketing ;
    rdfs:label 'Campaign Contribution' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the participation of real estate workforce personnel in marketing campaigns. It captures the specific role, time allocation, and contribution period for each employee working on each campaign. Each record links one employee to one campaign with attributes that exist only in the context of this working relationship, enabling tracking of multi-disciplinary campaign teams and individual workload allocation across concurrent campaigns.. Existence Justification: In real estate marketing operations, campaigns require multi-disciplinary teams where a single employee (e.g., a listing agent) works across multiple concurrent campaigns, and each campaign engages multiple employees in different roles (photographer, copywriter, marketing coordinator, lead agent). The business actively manages these assignments with specific role definitions, time allocation percentages, and contribution periods that are tracked, updated, and reported on as operational data.' .

ind:ListingDisclosure rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Listing Disclosure' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the compliance relationship between property listings and regulatory disclosure requirements. It captures the fulfillment status of each mandatory disclosure requirement for each listing, tracking completion dates, responsible parties, evidence documentation, and any waivers or exceptions. Each record links one listing to one compliance requirement with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific listing-requirement pairing.. Existence Justification: In real estate brokerage operations, each property listing must satisfy multiple mandatory disclosure requirements that vary by jurisdiction, property type, and transaction type (e.g., lead paint disclosure for pre-1978 residential, environmental hazard disclosure for commercial, agency disclosure for all, fair housing posting requirements). Conversely, each compliance requirement applies to many listings across the portfolio. Brokerages actively manage per-listing disclosure completion, tracking status, completion dates, responsible parties, and evidence documentation for each listing-requirement pairing as part of the listing lifecycle and transaction closing process.' .

ind:NavAppraisalInput rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Valuation ;
    rdfs:label 'Nav Appraisal Input' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the inclusion of a specific appraisal report in a Net Asset Value (NAV) calculation. It captures which appraisals were used as valuation inputs for portfolio-level NAV calculations, the specific value drawn from each appraisal, the weight assigned to that appraisal in the aggregation, and whether adjustments were applied. Each record links one NAV calculation to one appraisal with attributes that exist only in the context of this relationship, supporting REIT financial reporting, investor transparency, and ASC 820 fair value hierarchy disclosures.. Existence Justification: In real estate investment management, NAV calculations are portfolio-level aggregations that draw on multiple individual property appraisals as valuation inputs. One NAV calculation incorporates many appraisals (across multiple properties in the portfolio), and one appraisal can be used in multiple NAV calculations over time (e.g., quarterly NAV runs for the same fund, or NAV calculations for multiple funds that own the same property). The business actively manages this relationship through valuation committees that select which appraisals to include, assign weights, and apply adjustments.' .

ind:OwnerRepresentation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Owner ;
    rdfs:label 'Owner Representation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the formal representation relationship between property owners/investors and licensed brokers. It captures the engagement terms, exclusivity arrangements, market focus, and relationship lifecycle for each owner-broker pairing. Each record links one owner to one broker with attributes that exist only in the context of this professional representation relationship, used for conflict-of-interest checks, commission tracking, deal assignment, and CRM workflows.. Existence Justification: In real estate brokerage operations, property owners and investors routinely engage multiple brokers across different markets, asset classes, and transaction types (e.g., one broker for multifamily acquisitions in Dallas, another for office dispositions in NYC). Simultaneously, brokers maintain active representation relationships with multiple owner clients, each with distinct engagement terms, exclusivity arrangements, and market focus areas. The business actively manages these representation relationships as formal engagements with lifecycle tracking, conflict-of-interest checks, commission overrides, and CRM workflows.' .

ind:Subscription rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Owner ;
    rdfs:label 'Subscription' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the contractual subscription relationship between an owner/investor and a real estate investment fund. It captures the investor\'s capital commitment, subscription terms, investor classification at the time of subscription, accreditation status verification, and side letter provisions. Each record represents a distinct subscription agreement linking one owner to one fund with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific investment commitment.. Existence Justification: In real estate fund operations, an owner/investor can subscribe to multiple funds (diversification across strategies, vintages, and asset classes), and each fund has multiple Limited Partner investors who have subscribed. Each subscription is a distinct contractual relationship with its own capital commitment, subscription date, investor class, fee terms (potentially customized via side letters), and accreditation verification. Fund administrators actively manage subscriptions as operational entities—tracking capital calls, distributions, investor reporting, K-1 generation, and waterfall calculations at the subscription level.' .

ind:Allocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Allocation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the contractual allocation of parking spaces to lease agreements. It captures the number of spaces reserved for each tenant under their lease, the applicable monthly rate, and the effective period of the allocation. Each record links one parking facility to one lease agreement with attributes that exist only in the context of this parking entitlement.. Existence Justification: In real estate lease administration, a single parking facility serves multiple tenants across different lease agreements, and a single lease agreement can allocate parking spaces from multiple facilities (e.g., surface lot + garage, or multiple buildings in a campus). The business actively manages parking allocations as contractual entitlements, tracking the number of spaces, negotiated rates, effective periods, and reservation status per tenant-per-facility. This is an operational relationship that lease administrators create, modify, and terminate as part of lease execution and amendment processes.' .

ind:PartsUsage rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Maintenance ;
    rdfs:label 'Parts Usage' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the consumption of maintenance parts against work orders in facility operations. It captures the operational event of issuing inventory items to fulfill maintenance work. Each record links one parts_inventory item to one work_order with attributes that exist only in the context of this consumption transaction: quantity issued, unit cost at time of issuance, issue date, returned quantity, and cost classification.. Existence Justification: In facility maintenance operations, parts usage represents the operational event of consuming inventory items to fulfill work orders. A single work order routinely requires multiple different parts (e.g., HVAC repair needs filters, belts, refrigerant), and a single part type is consumed across many different work orders over time. CMMS platforms like Building Engines explicitly model this as a parts usage or materials used transaction entity with its own attributes (quantity, cost at issuance, date, returns).' .

ind:BrokerCommission rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Broker Commission' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the commission assignment between a property sale transaction and a broker. It captures the specific role, representation side, and commission economics for each broker involved in a property sale transaction. Each record links one property_sale to one broker with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific transaction participation.. Existence Justification: In real estate transactions, a single property sale involves multiple brokers in different roles (listing broker, buyer\'s broker, co-brokers, referral brokers), and each broker participates in many property sales throughout their career. The business actively manages broker commission assignments as operational records, tracking each broker\'s specific role, representation type, commission split percentage, and payment status for each transaction. This is not an analytical correlation but an operational business process where commission assignments are created, approved, and paid as distinct business events.' .

ind:SaleAttribution rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Transaction ;
    rdfs:label 'Sale Attribution' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the multi-touch marketing attribution between property sales and marketing campaigns. It captures the contribution of each campaign to a completed property sale, enabling ROI analysis and marketing effectiveness measurement. Each record links one property_sale to one campaign with attribution metrics that exist only in the context of this relationship.. Existence Justification: In real estate marketing operations, a single property sale is routinely attributed to multiple marketing campaigns through multi-touch attribution models (e.g., awareness campaign, retargeting campaign, open house promotion, MLS syndication). Conversely, a single campaign drives multiple property sales across its lifecycle. Marketing teams actively manage and analyze these attribution relationships to calculate campaign ROI, optimize budget allocation, and measure marketing effectiveness. This is an operational business process, not an analytical correlation.' .

ind:PolicyAssignment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Insurance ;
    rdfs:label 'Policy Assignment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the assignment or transfer of insurance policies during property sale transactions. It captures the relationship between a property sale and the insurance policies that must be assigned, transferred, or replaced at closing. Each record links one property_sale to one policy with attributes that exist only in the context of the closing transaction, including assignment status, effective dates, proration calculations, and lender notification requirements.. Existence Justification: In real estate transactions, a property sale can involve multiple insurance policies that must be assigned or transferred at closing (e.g., property hazard, title insurance, flood, general liability, umbrella coverage). Conversely, in portfolio sales or bulk transactions, a single master insurance policy can cover multiple properties being sold across different transactions. The assignment of each policy at closing is an operational business process managed by closing coordinators, with specific attributes like assignment status, effective date, proration amount, and lender notification requirements that belong to the relationship itself, not to either the sale or the policy alone.' .

ind:ProgramPropertyTypeCoverage rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Reference ;
    rdfs:label 'Program Property Type Coverage' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the underwriting coverage configuration between property_type and insurance_program. It captures the specific coverage requirements, limits, endorsements, and exclusions that apply when a particular property type is included in an insurance program. Each record links one property_type to one insurance_program with underwriting parameters that exist only in the context of this relationship. This is an operational underwriting design artifact created during program structuring and renewal processes.. Existence Justification: Insurance programs in real estate cover portfolios containing multiple property types (office, retail, industrial, multifamily, land), and each property type appears across multiple insurance programs over different policy years and portfolio segments. The underwriting process requires risk managers to define specific coverage requirements, minimum limits, mandatory endorsements, exclusions, and rate tiers for each property type within each program. This is an operational underwriting design activity performed during program structuring and renewal.' .

ind:SpaceCampaignInclusion rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Space Campaign Inclusion' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the marketing inclusion relationship between a leasable space and a marketing campaign. It captures the time-bounded participation of a specific space in a campaign, including the asking rent at the time of marketing, the space\'s status during the campaign period, and its priority within the campaign\'s portfolio of marketed spaces. Each record links one space to one campaign with attributes that exist only in the context of this marketing relationship.. Existence Justification: In commercial real estate marketing operations, a single leasable space can be simultaneously marketed across multiple campaigns (e.g., broker outreach, digital advertising, open house events, MLS syndication), and each campaign typically promotes multiple available spaces across the portfolio. Marketing teams actively manage which spaces are included in which campaigns, tracking inclusion dates, the asking rent being advertised, marketing status per space-campaign combination, and priority rankings to allocate budget and creative prominence.' .

ind:RoleTrainingRequirement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Role Training Requirement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the formal assignment of mandatory or recommended training courses to job profiles within the real estate enterprise. It captures regulatory CE requirements, compliance mandates, and professional development standards that apply to specific roles. Each record links one training course to one job profile with attributes that define the requirement\'s nature, timing, and applicability. Sourced from ADP Workforce Now LMS and HCM modules, this association supports compliance tracking, license renewal planning, and onboarding curriculum design.. Existence Justification: In real estate workforce management, training requirements are formally assigned to job profiles based on regulatory mandates (state real estate commission CE requirements for brokers, appraisal board requirements for appraisers), compliance policies (Fair Housing, OSHA), and role-specific competencies. A single training course (e.g., Fair Housing Act compliance) is required for multiple job profiles (broker, property manager, leasing agent), and a single job profile requires multiple training courses to maintain licensure and operational competency. This is an actively managed business process in ADP Workforce Now LMS, where HR and compliance teams create, update, and retire training requirements as regulations and business needs evolve.' .

ind:UnderwritingInput rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Underwriting Input' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the underwriting input relationship between executed or comparable lease agreements and development pro forma financial models. It captures which leases inform which pro forma scenarios, the role each lease plays in the underwriting (anchor pre-lease, comparable, in-place for value-add), and the specific financial assumptions derived from each lease. Each record links one lease agreement to one pro forma with attributes that exist only in the context of this underwriting relationship. Critical for investment committee due diligence, lender underwriting packages, and audit trails showing how pro forma rent and occupancy assumptions were derived.. Existence Justification: In real estate development underwriting, a single pro forma scenario references multiple lease agreements as inputs (anchor pre-leases that drive NOI projections, comparable leases that establish market rent benchmarks, and in-place leases for value-add acquisitions). Conversely, a single executed or comparable lease can inform multiple pro forma scenarios across different projects, sensitivity cases (base/upside/downside), or pro forma versions as assumptions evolve. Investment committees and lenders require audit trails showing which leases informed which assumptions, making this a managed operational relationship, not an analytical correlation.' .

ind:LeaseRepresentation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Lease Representation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the brokerage representation relationship between a lease agreement and a broker. It captures which brokers represented which parties in a lease transaction, their commission arrangements, and their specific role in the deal. Each record links one lease agreement to one broker with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific representation engagement.. Existence Justification: In real estate brokerage operations, a single lease agreement routinely involves multiple brokers representing different parties (landlord-side broker, tenant-side broker, and potentially co-brokers on either side). Each broker handles many lease agreements throughout their career. The business actively manages these representation relationships as distinct operational records, tracking each broker\'s side, commission split, role, and payment status for every deal.' .

ind:CollateralAssignment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Collateral Assignment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the collateral assignment relationship between lease agreements and debt facilities in real estate finance. It captures the legal and operational assignment of lease rents as collateral security for debt instruments. Each record links one lease agreement to one debt facility with attributes that exist only in the context of this collateral relationship, including assignment dates, recording status, lender consent requirements, and subordination hierarchy.. Existence Justification: In commercial real estate finance, a single debt facility is routinely collateralized by multiple lease agreements (assignment of rents across all tenants on a property or portfolio), and a single lease agreement can be assigned as collateral to multiple debt facilities simultaneously (e.g., senior mortgage + mezzanine debt, or across refinancing events where subordination agreements preserve junior lender positions). Lenders actively manage these collateral assignments as distinct operational records with legal recording requirements, subordination hierarchies, consent workflows, and collateral coverage calculations.' .

ind:CoverageRequirement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Lease ;
    rdfs:label 'Coverage Requirement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the insurance coverage requirement relationship between lease agreements and insurance policies. It captures the specific insurance compliance obligations that each lease agreement imposes, and tracks which policies satisfy those requirements. Each record links one lease agreement to one insurance policy with attributes that exist only in the context of this compliance relationship, including the type of coverage required by the lease, the minimum coverage limits mandated, compliance status, and verification dates.. Existence Justification: In real estate lease administration, a single lease agreement routinely requires multiple types of insurance coverage (general liability, property, workers compensation, umbrella, and specialty coverages like flood or terrorism), and each of these requirements may be satisfied by a different policy. Conversely, a single blanket insurance policy—particularly master property policies or portfolio-wide general liability policies—commonly covers multiple lease agreements across a property portfolio. Lease administrators actively manage this many-to-many relationship by tracking compliance status, verifying coverage limits against lease requirements, maintaining certificates of insurance, and monitoring expiration dates for each lease-policy pairing.' .

ind:DealAsset rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Deal Asset' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the inclusion of a specific asset within an investment deal pipeline. It captures the underwriting, due diligence, and allocation details that exist only in the context of a specific asset being evaluated or transacted within a specific deal. Each record links one asset to one investment deal with attributes such as allocated underwritten value, due diligence status, allocation percentage, and asset-specific deal roles (e.g., anchor asset, portfolio filler, value-add component).. Existence Justification: In real estate investment operations, a single asset can appear in multiple competing deal scenarios simultaneously (e.g., multiple bidders, different portfolio configurations, disposition vs. hold analysis), and portfolio acquisition deals routinely involve multiple assets under a single transaction structure. Investment teams actively manage the deal-asset relationship by tracking per-asset underwritten values, due diligence findings, allocation percentages, and strategic roles (anchor vs. filler) that exist only in the deal context.' .

ind:AssetAuditScope rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Property ;
    rdfs:label 'Asset Audit Scope' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the inclusion of specific real estate assets within formal audit engagement scopes. It captures the operational reality that audit engagements cover multiple properties across the portfolio, and individual assets are subject to multiple audit engagements over time (annual audits, acquisition due diligence, disposition audits, regulatory examinations). Each record links one asset to one audit engagement with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific audit scope inclusion — the reason the asset was selected for review, the risk rating assigned to that asset within this particular engagement, the number of findings specific to that asset, and the date the asset was formally included in scope.. Existence Justification: In real estate audit operations, audit engagements routinely cover multiple properties across the portfolio (portfolio-wide SOX audits, regulatory examinations, internal control reviews), and individual assets are subject to multiple audit engagements over time (annual financial audits, acquisition due diligence audits, disposition audits, ESG audits, regulatory examinations). The business actively manages audit scope as an operational process — compliance teams define which assets are in scope for each engagement, assign asset-specific risk ratings, track asset-specific findings, and allocate auditor resources at the asset level within each engagement.' .

ind:BrokerMarketCoverage rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Brokerage ;
    rdfs:label 'Broker Market Coverage' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the territory assignment between broker and geographic_hierarchy. It captures the formal designation of which geographic markets a broker is authorized and assigned to cover for lead routing, listing assignments, and production tracking. Each record links one broker to one geographic market node with attributes that define the nature and period of that market coverage assignment.. Existence Justification: In real estate brokerage operations, brokers are assigned to cover multiple geographic markets (MSAs, submarkets, cities, zip codes) simultaneously for lead routing and territory management, and each market has multiple brokers assigned with different coverage roles (primary, secondary, backup). The brokerage actively manages these territory assignments as operational records with effective dates, designation types, and coverage status to drive lead distribution and production reporting by market.' .

